WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:08.733
[Oh my god]

00:00:13.333 --> 00:00:14.466
[Oh my god]

00:00:15.600 --> 00:00:16.866
[Apologize in the snow, record Curry!]

00:00:22.566 --> 00:00:25.966
[Twinkle Love in Winter]

00:00:28.700 --> 00:00:29.800
It's so beautiful here.

00:00:30.266 --> 00:00:31.166
Just like you all,

00:00:31.633 --> 00:00:32.866
my journey

00:00:32.900 --> 00:00:34.233
starts here.

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:36.633
[Twinkle Winter Check-in Sheet]

00:00:36.633 --> 00:00:38.433
Honestly, every fill-in-the-blank

00:00:38.833 --> 00:00:41.466
is an open-book test on life.

00:00:42.700 --> 00:00:44.266
Some answers are like

00:00:44.300 --> 00:00:46.633
that perfect moment in a shot.

00:00:47.633 --> 00:00:48.866
You don't hesitate

00:00:48.900 --> 00:00:50.400
to write down the only answer.

00:00:50.833 --> 00:00:52.133
And some answers

00:00:52.133 --> 00:00:53.966
always seem hard to pin down.

00:00:54.933 --> 00:00:57.766
Like trying to color a shadow.

00:00:59.533 --> 00:01:00.900
But what does that matter?

00:01:01.333 --> 00:01:03.233
You can always erase and rewrite.

00:01:04.900 --> 00:01:12.200
[EP03 Fill-in-the-Blanks]

00:01:12.866 --> 00:01:15.000
Do you think there's a new guest today?

00:01:15.033 --> 00:01:16.766
Why are you all asking that?

00:01:16.800 --> 00:01:17.833
Jason was asking just now too.

00:01:19.600 --> 00:01:20.866
[Just curious]

00:01:21.700 --> 00:01:23.500
[The board's been updated]

00:01:23.866 --> 00:01:24.300
Really?

00:01:24.300 --> 00:01:25.233
[Urumqi Romeo Miyue Guesthouse]
Inform everyone.

00:01:25.266 --> 00:01:25.966
Let's go check it out.

00:01:26.700 --> 00:01:27.033
What?

00:01:27.633 --> 00:01:28.966
Let's go.

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:29.266
Come on.

00:01:30.200 --> 00:01:32.433
Hello, it's the new millennium now.

00:01:32.433 --> 00:01:33.500
[Video. Notice. DV cam]
Open the iPad

00:01:33.500 --> 00:01:35.366
to check today's study tour schedule.

00:01:35.933 --> 00:01:37.566
Come quick, there's a video here.

00:01:37.600 --> 00:01:38.233
Okay.

00:01:39.300 --> 00:01:41.666
Important notice.

00:01:41.700 --> 00:01:42.733
[Totally stunned]

00:01:42.966 --> 00:01:44.500
Important notice.

00:01:44.533 --> 00:01:45.533
This is so retro.

00:01:45.533 --> 00:01:47.466
Everyone, grab the DV cam

00:01:47.500 --> 00:01:49.000
and put on your uniforms.

00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:49.700
Let's

00:01:49.733 --> 00:01:52.133
go to school together.

00:01:53.100 --> 00:01:53.766
That's it?

00:01:53.800 --> 00:01:54.333
[Still wanting more]

00:01:54.466 --> 00:01:54.900
Oh my,

00:01:54.900 --> 00:01:57.233
it feels like my childhood nightmare.

00:01:57.266 --> 00:01:58.500
[In unison]
School again.

00:01:58.633 --> 00:02:00.166
[I love school the most.]

00:02:00.200 --> 00:02:00.833
Let's go.

00:02:00.833 --> 00:02:01.300
Come on.

00:02:01.333 --> 00:02:01.766
Let's go.

00:02:01.766 --> 00:02:03.366
Move.

00:02:04.433 --> 00:02:05.633
That's the bus, right?

00:02:06.500 --> 00:02:07.566
[Balou Station]

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:11.833
Is it a toy?

00:02:12.700 --> 00:02:13.500
Yo-yo.

00:02:13.500 --> 00:02:14.533
[There are yo-yos?]

00:02:14.566 --> 00:02:16.566
[Welcome to the Millennium era.]

00:02:18.333 --> 00:02:19.166
[Yo-yo]

00:02:19.200 --> 00:02:20.433
Yo-yo.

00:02:20.433 --> 00:02:22.033
[Bubble glue]
This was my favorite.

00:02:22.566 --> 00:02:23.100
[Virtual pet]

00:02:23.100 --> 00:02:23.900
This one's fun.

00:02:24.333 --> 00:02:26.233
[Bamboo-copter. Bakugan]

00:02:27.233 --> 00:02:27.733
What's this?

00:02:28.833 --> 00:02:29.733
I want the yo-yo seat.

00:02:31.400 --> 00:02:32.266
Then I'll sit with you.

00:02:32.266 --> 00:02:32.933
Okay.

00:02:32.933 --> 00:02:33.566
[Lily sits next to Sean.]

00:02:34.033 --> 00:02:35.100
Are you sitting on the inside?

00:02:35.100 --> 00:02:36.500
Where do you want to sit?

00:02:36.500 --> 00:02:37.133
Sure.

00:02:37.133 --> 00:02:38.533
[Eon sits next to Zhaoyu Zhang.]

00:02:38.733 --> 00:02:40.166
Wait a second.

00:02:40.600 --> 00:02:41.300
You go first.

00:02:41.300 --> 00:02:42.533
[Two seats left.]

00:02:42.933 --> 00:02:43.566
I'm good with either.

00:02:43.600 --> 00:02:44.266
Go ahead.

00:02:44.933 --> 00:02:45.700
[Being polite]
Go ahead.

00:02:46.300 --> 00:02:46.966
You want me to choose?

00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:47.866
[Both insisting]
You choose.

00:02:47.866 --> 00:02:48.666
Come on.

00:02:49.600 --> 00:02:50.433
A tough choice?

00:02:50.433 --> 00:02:51.733
Why are you struggling to choose?

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:53.100
[Totally confused]

00:02:53.200 --> 00:02:53.433
Hurry.

00:02:53.433 --> 00:02:53.966
[Hurry]

00:02:54.000 --> 00:02:54.933
[Either is fine.]
Hurry.

00:02:54.933 --> 00:02:55.400
Either will do.

00:02:55.433 --> 00:02:57.866
Are we two that unwanted?

00:02:58.000 --> 00:02:59.400
[Not my problem]

00:02:59.866 --> 00:03:01.200
Come on, stop messing around.

00:03:01.233 --> 00:03:01.933
Hurry up.

00:03:01.933 --> 00:03:02.333
Cut it out.

00:03:02.333 --> 00:03:02.933
Rock, paper, scissors.

00:03:02.933 --> 00:03:04.633
Whoever loses picks first.

00:03:04.666 --> 00:03:06.333
[Is this a penalty?]
The loser picks first?

00:03:07.800 --> 00:03:11.500
Rock-paper-scissors.

00:03:11.500 --> 00:03:12.233
[Yuna wins]
Okay.

00:03:12.933 --> 00:03:13.833
Where should I sit?

00:03:14.533 --> 00:03:15.733
[Hesitates to speak]

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:17.066
[Makes room]

00:03:17.100 --> 00:03:18.100
You sit first.

00:03:21.433 --> 00:03:22.900
[Stares]

00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:26.600
Go for it.

00:03:27.400 --> 00:03:29.200
[Looks at Nora again.]

00:03:31.166 --> 00:03:33.033
[Nora sits next to Hao Chen.]

00:03:35.700 --> 00:03:37.833
[Everyone watches the drama.]

00:03:38.600 --> 00:03:39.300
Then I'll sit here.

00:03:39.300 --> 00:03:40.033
[Turns around]

00:03:41.400 --> 00:03:42.633
So did you win or lose?

00:03:44.233 --> 00:03:45.700
I didn't see your rock-paper-scissors.

00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:51.433
[Looks out the window]

00:03:52.033 --> 00:03:54.100
[Looks around]

00:03:54.433 --> 00:03:56.066
[Plays with the toy in hand]

00:04:00.200 --> 00:04:01.433
[Breaks the silence]
What'd you play as a kid?

00:04:02.400 --> 00:04:03.266
Barbie doll.

00:04:04.500 --> 00:04:05.533
And that Slap Game.

00:04:05.533 --> 00:04:06.933
The one for reflexes.

00:04:06.933 --> 00:04:07.566
Yeah.

00:04:08.633 --> 00:04:09.133
No.

00:04:09.600 --> 00:04:11.233
[Jokes first]
She'd smack from above.

00:04:11.233 --> 00:04:12.566
[Voice cracks]
I did not.

00:04:12.600 --> 00:04:14.033
She never even lowered it.

00:04:14.033 --> 00:04:15.033
I did not.

00:04:16.600 --> 00:04:17.700
Let's do a rough version.

00:04:17.700 --> 00:04:18.366
So gentle.

00:04:19.833 --> 00:04:20.633
Okay.

00:04:22.233 --> 00:04:23.866
[Laughs behind hand]
So funny.

00:04:23.866 --> 00:04:24.866
Want to try it?

00:04:24.866 --> 00:04:25.300
Sure.

00:04:25.300 --> 00:04:26.633
[Invites Sean over]

00:04:28.433 --> 00:04:29.500
You can react fast.

00:04:30.466 --> 00:04:30.900
Like this.

00:04:31.100 --> 00:04:32.033
[Ask Eon to join the game]
Both hands?

00:04:32.033 --> 00:04:32.866
Yeah, both hands.

00:04:32.866 --> 00:04:33.133
One.

00:04:34.300 --> 00:04:36.233
Again. Three, two, one.

00:04:37.466 --> 00:04:39.100
Three, two, one.

00:04:39.666 --> 00:04:40.300
Got you.

00:04:40.900 --> 00:04:42.333
From your

00:04:43.000 --> 00:04:45.533
tiny little movements,

00:04:45.533 --> 00:04:46.133
I could tell.

00:04:46.133 --> 00:04:46.733
Come on.

00:04:49.433 --> 00:04:50.033
Wait a sec.

00:04:52.300 --> 00:04:53.433
Okay.

00:04:53.466 --> 00:04:54.200
Come on, keep going.

00:04:55.466 --> 00:04:56.566
It's all red.

00:04:56.600 --> 00:04:57.300
They went all out.

00:04:58.100 --> 00:04:58.766
No.

00:05:01.233 --> 00:05:01.733
I'll use the DV

00:05:01.733 --> 00:05:03.000
to film you guys.

00:05:03.033 --> 00:05:03.766
[Picks up the camcorder to film.]

00:05:05.733 --> 00:05:06.633
This one's blown up.

00:05:09.666 --> 00:05:10.800
It's shaped like a heart.

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:14.000
Anyone want my little balloon?

00:05:14.033 --> 00:05:15.233
Who'd want it anyway?

00:05:15.233 --> 00:05:16.266
[I do.]

00:05:16.433 --> 00:05:18.066
Who wants it? It's all drool.

00:05:19.000 --> 00:05:20.166
I'm gonna stomp it flat.

00:05:21.566 --> 00:05:22.566
Just a tiny bit off.

00:05:24.200 --> 00:05:25.100
It's so cute.

00:05:25.100 --> 00:05:26.133
I can't hold it much longer.

00:05:26.533 --> 00:05:27.200
I'm gonna throw it.

00:05:27.233 --> 00:05:27.833
Go ahead.

00:05:28.600 --> 00:05:30.066
No, don't toss the whole thing.

00:05:31.300 --> 00:05:31.966
So good.

00:05:31.966 --> 00:05:32.666
It really looks like it.

00:05:32.666 --> 00:05:33.200
Really?

00:05:33.333 --> 00:05:33.766
Yeah.

00:05:33.800 --> 00:05:35.233
What's this?

00:05:35.233 --> 00:05:36.066
A heart.

00:05:36.900 --> 00:05:38.000
I thought it was a liver.

00:05:39.600 --> 00:05:40.700
Hello.

00:05:40.700 --> 00:05:41.533
Hi.

00:05:41.566 --> 00:05:42.233
Hello.

00:05:42.233 --> 00:05:42.900
Hey, everyone.

00:05:42.900 --> 00:05:44.566
Hello, hello.

00:05:45.433 --> 00:05:46.066
Wow.

00:05:46.800 --> 00:05:47.400
Keep up with me.

00:05:47.700 --> 00:05:48.600
I'm right behind you.

00:05:50.100 --> 00:05:51.633
You all look so energetic.

00:05:52.633 --> 00:05:53.566
I'm gonna cry.

00:05:53.600 --> 00:05:54.800
This is so touching.

00:05:55.666 --> 00:05:57.000
[Xinjiang University]
Hilarious.

00:06:08.600 --> 00:06:11.733
[Youhao Campus of Xinjiang University]

00:06:14.466 --> 00:06:15.766
Then I'll take the back row.

00:06:15.800 --> 00:06:16.933
I want this seat.

00:06:16.933 --> 00:06:17.766
[Lounge Area. Being Asked Area.
Top Student Area]

00:06:17.800 --> 00:06:19.433
Then I'll sit here.

00:06:19.433 --> 00:06:20.066
Excuse me.

00:06:20.066 --> 00:06:21.400
I like the front row in class.

00:06:22.200 --> 00:06:23.533
[Top student seat]

00:06:23.600 --> 00:06:24.433
Then I'll sit...

00:06:24.433 --> 00:06:25.733
on the side, I guess.

00:06:25.733 --> 00:06:27.000
I want that one, by the window.

00:06:27.733 --> 00:06:29.400
[They look over at once]

00:06:31.200 --> 00:06:32.933
[Hesitates]

00:06:39.233 --> 00:06:40.666
[Steps in first]

00:06:43.133 --> 00:06:43.600
[Still hesitating]

00:06:43.633 --> 00:06:45.133
Then I'll...

00:06:46.833 --> 00:06:48.566
[Walks straight to the front row]

00:06:48.733 --> 00:06:50.200
[Glances over]

00:06:50.433 --> 00:06:51.866
[Sits in the front row]

00:06:55.200 --> 00:06:56.466
Maybe the back is better.

00:06:56.466 --> 00:06:57.366
[Sits in the corner]

00:07:01.200 --> 00:07:02.100
There's one seat left.

00:07:02.800 --> 00:07:04.900
[Waiting for someone]

00:07:04.933 --> 00:07:06.400
A guy or a girl?

00:07:07.600 --> 00:07:08.866
No idea.

00:07:08.866 --> 00:07:09.966
I'm really curious.

00:07:11.100 --> 00:07:12.600
About the new classmate?

00:07:12.900 --> 00:07:14.100
[Let me take a look]

00:07:14.100 --> 00:07:14.800
Someone's coming.

00:07:15.733 --> 00:07:16.233
Are they here?

00:07:16.266 --> 00:07:16.966
Who?

00:07:22.900 --> 00:07:24.300
Can we check it out?

00:07:24.300 --> 00:07:25.166
Let's go take a look.

00:07:25.200 --> 00:07:25.833
[Go greet them first]

00:07:26.066 --> 00:07:26.700
Anyone here?

00:07:28.600 --> 00:07:29.600
No one's here.

00:07:29.600 --> 00:07:30.233
Nobody.

00:07:34.733 --> 00:07:35.800
Let's pretend to be the teacher.

00:07:35.833 --> 00:07:36.533
Who's gonna play the teacher?

00:07:36.533 --> 00:07:37.533
Who'd dare?

00:07:38.100 --> 00:07:39.200
[Let's surprise the new classmate]
Who wants to pretend to be the teacher?

00:07:39.500 --> 00:07:40.633
[It's you.]

00:07:40.633 --> 00:07:42.300
You look the part.

00:07:42.300 --> 00:07:43.600
This one.

00:07:43.633 --> 00:07:44.733
Scare the new classmate a little.

00:07:46.800 --> 00:07:47.900
[Intimidate]

00:07:47.933 --> 00:07:49.000
This one looks right.

00:07:49.400 --> 00:07:50.033
This one looks right.

00:07:52.300 --> 00:07:53.333
This one looks right.

00:07:53.333 --> 00:07:53.933
[Intimidate]

00:07:58.333 --> 00:07:59.333
Hello, miss.

00:08:00.033 --> 00:08:01.500
[The real teacher is here.]

00:08:01.533 --> 00:08:02.633
Hello, class.

00:08:03.233 --> 00:08:04.333
[Intimidated]
Hello, miss.

00:08:04.900 --> 00:08:05.500
Hi, everyone.

00:08:06.033 --> 00:08:06.666
Go ahead and sit down.

00:08:07.866 --> 00:08:08.366
That was rude.

00:08:08.400 --> 00:08:09.400
I shouldn't have taken it off.

00:08:11.800 --> 00:08:13.400
[Glad it wasn't me.]

00:08:14.300 --> 00:08:15.233
Hello, students.

00:08:15.266 --> 00:08:17.166
I'm your homeroom teacher today.

00:08:17.200 --> 00:08:18.366
[Yu Zhiling, Psychological Counselor]

00:08:18.400 --> 00:08:19.666
[Postdoctoral Researcher
in Zhejiang University]

00:08:19.666 --> 00:08:21.400
If you've watched earlier seasons

00:08:21.433 --> 00:08:21.933
of Twinkle Love,

00:08:21.933 --> 00:08:23.933
you've probably seen me
in the observation room

00:08:23.933 --> 00:08:26.200
I'm a relationship advisor.

00:08:26.233 --> 00:08:29.233
[Yuna]
First, I'd like to get to know you a bit.

00:08:29.233 --> 00:08:31.666
Let's play a quick game.

00:08:31.800 --> 00:08:32.700
I know

00:08:32.700 --> 00:08:35.100
you're already familiar with each other.

00:08:35.100 --> 00:08:36.933
Could you try

00:08:36.933 --> 00:08:39.666
to use four words

00:08:39.700 --> 00:08:41.633
to describe your partner beside you?

00:08:42.133 --> 00:08:43.366
[Come on, my partner.]

00:08:44.033 --> 00:08:44.566
Let's do it.

00:08:44.600 --> 00:08:45.433
[No problem]
Okay.

00:08:46.100 --> 00:08:47.733
[Who wants to describe me?]

00:08:47.733 --> 00:08:49.400
Okay, who's ready?

00:08:49.433 --> 00:08:50.633
Raise your hand and let me know.

00:08:51.800 --> 00:08:52.600
Okay, you go ahead.

00:08:54.900 --> 00:08:56.000
Central plains sweetie.

00:08:56.033 --> 00:08:57.866
[Central Plains Sweetie]

00:08:58.333 --> 00:09:00.566
[Can we be more original?]
That's a bit too expected.

00:09:02.866 --> 00:09:03.400
Anything else?

00:09:03.833 --> 00:09:04.333
You got one?

00:09:04.333 --> 00:09:05.166
Yeah, I got one.

00:09:05.200 --> 00:09:06.033
This student.

00:09:06.733 --> 00:09:07.633
If it has to be four words,

00:09:07.666 --> 00:09:09.100
then I'd call him

00:09:09.100 --> 00:09:11.033
[Basketball Star]

00:09:11.133 --> 00:09:12.300
[Yep, that's me.]

00:09:12.300 --> 00:09:14.400
Because he really loves basketball.

00:09:15.000 --> 00:09:16.033
And

00:09:16.033 --> 00:09:16.866
his name is Eon.

00:09:17.466 --> 00:09:18.300
My name is Zhaoyu Zhang.

00:09:21.466 --> 00:09:23.000
Okay, who else wants to go?

00:09:23.033 --> 00:09:24.033
If you're ready, raise your hand.

00:09:24.800 --> 00:09:25.500
Okay, you go ahead.

00:09:26.333 --> 00:09:28.533
Ms. Yu, his name is Hao Chen.

00:09:28.533 --> 00:09:29.633
And his...

00:09:29.666 --> 00:09:31.066
The four words

00:09:31.066 --> 00:09:32.366
to describe him are

00:09:32.400 --> 00:09:33.500
Millennium Prince.

00:09:33.666 --> 00:09:35.233
[Millennium Prince]

00:09:38.366 --> 00:09:39.633
[Hi, I'm Star.]

00:09:39.633 --> 00:09:40.500
[Star and Prince]

00:09:40.566 --> 00:09:41.200
[Prince facepalms.]

00:09:41.233 --> 00:09:43.066
Because he was born in 2000.

00:09:43.633 --> 00:09:44.300
Nice one.

00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:48.033
This student's name is Yuna.

00:09:48.033 --> 00:09:49.833
The phrase I'd use is

00:09:49.833 --> 00:09:51.866
Sunshine Girl.

00:09:52.300 --> 00:09:53.100
[Sunshine Girl]

00:09:53.100 --> 00:09:54.900
Because she's like a little sun,

00:09:54.900 --> 00:09:55.433
always shining on

00:09:55.466 --> 00:09:58.100
everyone in our class.

00:09:58.100 --> 00:09:59.366
She's warm.

00:09:59.400 --> 00:10:00.066
Okay.

00:10:00.066 --> 00:10:01.300
Okay, who wants to go next?

00:10:02.500 --> 00:10:04.333
The one sitting next to me is

00:10:04.333 --> 00:10:05.400
Nora.

00:10:05.433 --> 00:10:07.500
The words I picked for her are
My Other Self.

00:10:07.500 --> 00:10:08.933
Because we're really alike.

00:10:08.933 --> 00:10:11.066
[My Other Self]
So she's another me.

00:10:11.666 --> 00:10:12.500
That's so sweet.

00:10:12.733 --> 00:10:13.600
I'm so touched.

00:10:14.733 --> 00:10:16.833
Next to me is Lily.

00:10:16.866 --> 00:10:19.100
The four words I chose for her are
Graceful Goddess.

00:10:19.100 --> 00:10:20.400
[Graceful Goddess]

00:10:20.433 --> 00:10:21.266
Because our goddess

00:10:21.266 --> 00:10:22.933
always stay poised and elegant.

00:10:24.066 --> 00:10:25.600
That really hits the feels.

00:10:26.266 --> 00:10:27.966
I want to describe the classmate
in front of me.

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:29.433
His name is Jason.

00:10:29.433 --> 00:10:30.733
The words I'd use for him are

00:10:30.733 --> 00:10:31.700
Cheerful Handsome.

00:10:31.733 --> 00:10:33.566
[Cheerful Handsome]

00:10:34.433 --> 00:10:37.100
And the one behind me is Sean.

00:10:37.100 --> 00:10:38.333
The phrase I thought of for him is

00:10:38.333 --> 00:10:39.033
soulmate.

00:10:39.433 --> 00:10:42.066
[Soulmate]

00:10:42.200 --> 00:10:43.266
[This is my]
soulmate.

00:10:45.033 --> 00:10:46.166
Soulmate.

00:10:46.600 --> 00:10:48.500
[Soulmate]

00:10:48.533 --> 00:10:49.766
What about me?

00:10:49.800 --> 00:10:50.500
Hey, what about me?

00:10:50.500 --> 00:10:50.933
[This prince is not happy.]

00:10:54.400 --> 00:10:55.466
You're a soulmate too.

00:10:55.933 --> 00:10:56.933
[Soulmate +1]
What about Eon?

00:10:56.933 --> 00:10:58.200
[Soulmate +2]
He's a soulmate too.

00:11:00.333 --> 00:11:01.800
[Just as I thought]
So many soulmates?

00:11:02.500 --> 00:11:03.600
Looks like you're really popular.

00:11:04.333 --> 00:11:06.566
[Jason and His Soulmates]

00:11:06.600 --> 00:11:07.733
And today,

00:11:07.733 --> 00:11:10.166
we've got a huge surprise.

00:11:10.200 --> 00:11:13.433
We're introducing a new classmate.

00:11:13.433 --> 00:11:15.266
[A new classmate for real]
A round of applause.

00:11:17.466 --> 00:11:18.100
They're coming.

00:11:22.633 --> 00:11:23.466
I'm so nervous.

00:11:23.466 --> 00:11:24.733
Who is it?

00:11:24.733 --> 00:11:25.800
I'm so curous.

00:11:25.833 --> 00:11:26.933
There's no one, right?

00:11:29.733 --> 00:11:30.866
Are they too nervous?

00:11:30.900 --> 00:11:31.700
Who should go bring them out?

00:11:35.933 --> 00:11:36.566
Are they here?

00:12:04.666 --> 00:12:05.566
Hi, everyone.

00:12:05.833 --> 00:12:07.466
[Hi]

00:12:08.300 --> 00:12:08.933
Hi, everyone.

00:12:09.766 --> 00:12:11.266
Hi, everyone. I'm Jack.

00:12:11.466 --> 00:12:12.600
Just call me Jack.

00:12:12.633 --> 00:12:14.366
As for why I was late this time...

00:12:14.400 --> 00:12:15.333
It was mainly because,

00:12:15.333 --> 00:12:16.933
first, I was studying for IELTS,

00:12:16.933 --> 00:12:17.466
and second,

00:12:17.500 --> 00:12:19.433
my thesis proposal defense was on.

00:12:19.466 --> 00:12:21.166
And I ended up being a bit late.

00:12:21.200 --> 00:12:22.700
I really love sports.

00:12:23.166 --> 00:12:26.466
[Sports I'm good at:
skiing, basketball, shooting, cycling]

00:12:30.033 --> 00:12:32.500
And I think a big reason

00:12:32.500 --> 00:12:33.433
is my family.

00:12:35.300 --> 00:12:37.033
We're actually a family of athletes.

00:12:37.066 --> 00:12:38.100
[Family of athletes]

00:12:38.166 --> 00:12:39.666
[Look up to]

00:12:40.600 --> 00:12:41.666
My oldest uncle

00:12:41.666 --> 00:12:43.100
was the country's

00:12:43.100 --> 00:12:44.933
trap shooting men's champion.

00:12:45.833 --> 00:12:46.333
[Wow]

00:12:46.333 --> 00:12:49.866
So that's why I love sports so much.

00:12:49.900 --> 00:12:51.800
And this time, I brought some stickers.

00:12:51.833 --> 00:12:54.366
[Prepared in advance:
stickers I designed]

00:12:54.600 --> 00:12:55.333
[Stickers I designed myself]

00:12:55.333 --> 00:12:57.933
Thank you.

00:12:58.900 --> 00:12:59.700
Did you design all of these?

00:12:59.700 --> 00:13:01.166
Yeah, they're super cute, right?

00:13:01.200 --> 00:13:01.633
You're so talented.

00:13:01.633 --> 00:13:02.666
This one really looks like you.

00:13:02.666 --> 00:13:03.900
Which one? This one?

00:13:05.200 --> 00:13:05.933
So cute.

00:13:06.400 --> 00:13:06.933
Thank you.

00:13:06.933 --> 00:13:07.666
No problem.

00:13:08.500 --> 00:13:09.133
Where did you stick yours?

00:13:09.666 --> 00:13:10.200
Same here.

00:13:10.233 --> 00:13:11.500
Let me see which ones you got.

00:13:11.500 --> 00:13:12.500
[Yuna's pick]
Mine is Diandian.

00:13:12.933 --> 00:13:14.533
You got Diandian?

00:13:14.533 --> 00:13:15.933
Diandian? What's Diandian?

00:13:15.933 --> 00:13:17.366
[That's me]
This one's cute.

00:13:17.400 --> 00:13:18.033
Thank you.

00:13:19.533 --> 00:13:20.566
That's amazing.

00:13:20.933 --> 00:13:24.000
[Yuna's choice]

00:13:24.033 --> 00:13:25.133
[Matching kitty]
I like this one.

00:13:25.133 --> 00:13:27.200
Okay, thanks, new classmate.

00:13:28.533 --> 00:13:29.766
Then I'll sit here, okay.

00:13:32.333 --> 00:13:34.633
Next up is literature class.

00:13:34.666 --> 00:13:35.900
Let's take a ten-minute break.

00:13:35.933 --> 00:13:37.266
Then class starts right away.

00:13:43.066 --> 00:13:43.700
Okay.

00:13:43.700 --> 00:13:44.500
[Well...]

00:13:44.566 --> 00:13:46.466
[Stares]

00:13:47.000 --> 00:13:48.233
[5 mins earlier]
Let's give him a welcome scare.

00:13:54.833 --> 00:13:56.266
[Umm]

00:13:59.533 --> 00:14:00.366
This is a little awkward.

00:14:00.400 --> 00:14:01.066
[Is this vibe right?]

00:14:01.066 --> 00:14:01.466
A little awkward.

00:14:01.466 --> 00:14:02.700
It's mainly because you're new

00:14:02.700 --> 00:14:04.900
and you came during class.

00:14:04.900 --> 00:14:05.166
Really?

00:14:05.200 --> 00:14:06.633
So we're all a bit reserved.

00:14:08.266 --> 00:14:08.966
Really?

00:14:09.033 --> 00:14:10.466
[Seriously?]

00:14:10.500 --> 00:14:11.933
It's fine.

00:14:11.933 --> 00:14:13.600
Forget about the class.

00:14:15.333 --> 00:14:16.233
[Instantly well-behaved]

00:14:17.933 --> 00:14:19.400
[Sits up straight]

00:14:22.466 --> 00:14:23.800
Were we all like this in high school?

00:14:23.833 --> 00:14:25.666
[Lowers voice without meaning to]

00:14:37.300 --> 00:14:38.533
[Hello, class.]

00:14:39.366 --> 00:14:40.400
[Hello, sir.]

00:14:44.433 --> 00:14:45.766
[Curious]

00:14:51.333 --> 00:14:52.666
Red beans grow in the south.

00:14:53.800 --> 00:14:54.466
Did you see that?

00:14:54.466 --> 00:14:56.066
[Yearning, Tang, Wang Wei]
The writing is so beautiful.

00:14:56.066 --> 00:14:57.533
Red beans grow in the south.

00:14:57.533 --> 00:14:58.933
How many sprigs bloom in spring?

00:14:58.933 --> 00:15:00.066
I hope you will gather more.

00:15:00.100 --> 00:15:01.366
For this is deepest yearning.

00:15:03.933 --> 00:15:05.000
Hello, class.

00:15:05.033 --> 00:15:06.833
Hello, sir.

00:15:06.833 --> 00:15:08.066
It's an honor

00:15:08.066 --> 00:15:10.300
to have this literature class
at Xinjiang University.

00:15:10.300 --> 00:15:10.966
[Li Bo, professor]

00:15:11.000 --> 00:15:13.400
[School of Chinese Language and Literature,
Nanjing Normal University]

00:15:13.400 --> 00:15:15.833
The room gives out
the exact literary vibe.

00:15:15.833 --> 00:15:17.233
I can honestly say

00:15:17.233 --> 00:15:19.566
right now, I feel a twinkle

00:15:19.600 --> 00:15:20.400
of excitement.

00:15:21.633 --> 00:15:23.333
Because it just hit me

00:15:23.333 --> 00:15:25.833
that in Chinese literature today,

00:15:25.866 --> 00:15:26.766
the top award,

00:15:26.800 --> 00:15:28.466
especially for novels.

00:15:28.466 --> 00:15:29.666
Do you know what is it?

00:15:30.266 --> 00:15:31.866
[Pop quiz: Top award in Chinese literature?]
The Mao Dun Literature Prize?

00:15:31.866 --> 00:15:32.600
Right.

00:15:33.233 --> 00:15:34.500
The Mao Dun Literature Prize.

00:15:35.300 --> 00:15:38.400
[It's one of China's highest literary honors]
Mr. Mao Dun was from the southern land.

00:15:38.433 --> 00:15:40.266
[to encourage outstanding novel writing.]
What else grows in the south?

00:15:40.266 --> 00:15:41.466
Red bean.

00:15:41.466 --> 00:15:44.300
Exactly. "Red beans grow in the south".

00:15:44.300 --> 00:15:47.100
"How many sprigs bloom in spring?"

00:15:47.100 --> 00:15:49.833
Do you know Crown Prince Zhaoming?

00:15:51.333 --> 00:15:52.533
He's from the Liang Dynasty,

00:15:52.533 --> 00:15:55.933
[Quick fact: Crown Prince Zhaoming]
the Wei and Jin period.

00:15:55.933 --> 00:15:57.766
[eldest son of Emperor Xiao Yan.]
But what does he have to do

00:15:57.800 --> 00:15:58.833
[He led Selections of Refined Literature.]
with red beans?

00:15:58.833 --> 00:16:00.466
If you studied design...

00:16:00.633 --> 00:16:02.200
[Caught off guard]

00:16:02.233 --> 00:16:04.433
And I asked you to design

00:16:04.433 --> 00:16:06.666
a piece on him and red bean...

00:16:06.666 --> 00:16:08.200
[Pop quiz: His link to red bean]

00:16:11.100 --> 00:16:12.400
[Umm]

00:16:13.100 --> 00:16:14.966
[Plant red bean]

00:16:15.000 --> 00:16:15.700
Plant red bean?

00:16:16.233 --> 00:16:17.433
That answer is spot-on.

00:16:17.533 --> 00:16:19.066
[Major saved]

00:16:19.400 --> 00:16:20.500
[Top student's approval]

00:16:20.633 --> 00:16:21.366
[No way, really?]

00:16:21.400 --> 00:16:23.500
Classic design major move.

00:16:23.500 --> 00:16:24.800
It matches the history too.

00:16:24.833 --> 00:16:27.033
When the prince was compiling
Selections of Refined Literature,

00:16:27.033 --> 00:16:30.766
he met a nun in Jiangyi, Wuxi,

00:16:30.800 --> 00:16:32.500
named Huiru.

00:16:32.500 --> 00:16:33.966
Huiru was also highly learned.

00:16:34.000 --> 00:16:36.200
As they got along,

00:16:36.200 --> 00:16:38.300
the prince realized that...

00:16:38.300 --> 00:16:39.500
[Xiao Tong and Nun Huiru]
I know.

00:16:39.533 --> 00:16:40.333
[fell for each other.]
Go on.

00:16:40.333 --> 00:16:41.433
[But bound by custom,]
Tell us.

00:16:41.466 --> 00:16:44.533
[they couldn't be together.]
She was a nun.

00:16:44.533 --> 00:16:46.066
She couldn't leave religious life.

00:16:46.100 --> 00:16:49.000
So they couldn't stay together?

00:16:50.200 --> 00:16:52.100
She's right.

00:16:52.100 --> 00:16:55.000
[After parting with Xiao Tong,]
Out of grief,

00:16:55.000 --> 00:16:57.400
[Huiru died of sorrow.]
Xiao Tong planted a red bean tree

00:16:57.433 --> 00:17:00.900
[Xiao Tong planted a tree as a memorial.]
beside her thatched hut.

00:17:01.866 --> 00:17:04.733
But if we go through the poem again...

00:17:04.733 --> 00:17:09.133
"Red beans grow in the south.
How many sprigs bloom in spring?"

00:17:09.133 --> 00:17:10.533
In "Ten Thousand Quatrains
of Tang Dynasty"

00:17:10.533 --> 00:17:12.033
complied in Song Dynasty,

00:17:12.066 --> 00:17:13.300
there is another version.

00:17:13.300 --> 00:17:16.833
Not "I hope you will gather more",

00:17:16.866 --> 00:17:21.100
but "I hope you will gather no more".

00:17:21.433 --> 00:17:23.700
[I hope you will gather no more?]

00:17:23.733 --> 00:17:27.766
Which do you think is better?
"I hope you will gather more"

00:17:27.800 --> 00:17:30.333
or "I hope you will gather no more."

00:17:30.333 --> 00:17:31.400
If I were Huiru,

00:17:31.433 --> 00:17:33.900
I would want him to gather no more.

00:17:33.900 --> 00:17:35.633
If I were Huiru...

00:17:35.666 --> 00:17:36.933
[Gather no more]
from her point of view,

00:17:36.933 --> 00:17:37.833
in her time,

00:17:37.866 --> 00:17:39.866
and with her status,

00:17:39.866 --> 00:17:41.166
he and I would not be a good match.

00:17:41.533 --> 00:17:42.766
So I would hope

00:17:42.800 --> 00:17:44.600
that if we were...

00:17:44.600 --> 00:17:46.666
kindred spirits in literature,

00:17:47.200 --> 00:17:49.466
it should stay in that moment.

00:17:50.133 --> 00:17:51.233
It should no go further

00:17:51.266 --> 00:17:53.200
because our positions do not match.

00:17:53.900 --> 00:17:58.000
It is a love doomed to fade away.

00:17:58.033 --> 00:17:59.966
I think "gather more" works better.

00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:01.633
[Support for "gather more"]
Each time

00:18:01.633 --> 00:18:02.666
they gather, they can recall...

00:18:02.666 --> 00:18:04.300
- their good old...
- I see.

00:18:04.300 --> 00:18:06.800
Each time you gather more,

00:18:06.833 --> 00:18:07.500
you'll think of me.

00:18:07.500 --> 00:18:08.133
Right.

00:18:08.133 --> 00:18:09.733
When they're in love,

00:18:09.733 --> 00:18:11.800
when they're in that relationship,

00:18:11.833 --> 00:18:13.733
it's "I hope you will gather more".

00:18:15.000 --> 00:18:15.866
But I think

00:18:15.866 --> 00:18:17.766
if it's still in relationship,

00:18:17.800 --> 00:18:19.666
with both persuading and gathering more,

00:18:19.666 --> 00:18:20.700
then the two of them

00:18:20.700 --> 00:18:23.800
must be confirming their feelings.

00:18:23.833 --> 00:18:25.100
That's still the heart aflutter stage.

00:18:25.100 --> 00:18:27.100
Right,
if it's that heart aflutter stage,

00:18:27.100 --> 00:18:29.700
they meet someone truly meant to be,

00:18:29.700 --> 00:18:33.333
and they're both
in the bloom of youth...

00:18:33.333 --> 00:18:35.000
They'd hope each other to gather more.

00:18:35.033 --> 00:18:36.333
Exactly.

00:18:36.333 --> 00:18:38.266
But if it reaches a heartbroken phase...

00:18:38.300 --> 00:18:40.566
Then stop gathering.

00:18:40.600 --> 00:18:41.666
Looks like in different stages,

00:18:42.633 --> 00:18:45.033
"gather" means different things, right?

00:18:45.033 --> 00:18:47.233
In Wang Wei's Collected Poems,

00:18:47.233 --> 00:18:48.500
its original title was...

00:18:51.000 --> 00:18:54.300
["Yearning" was first titled "To Li Guinian on the River".]
To Li Guinian...

00:18:54.333 --> 00:18:56.466
[It was written by Wang Wei for his friend Li Guinian.]
on the River.

00:18:56.500 --> 00:18:58.633
Does this remind you of another poem

00:18:58.666 --> 00:19:00.933
we learned in elementary school?

00:19:00.933 --> 00:19:02.633
[Elementary school again?]
Its title also has Li Guinian.

00:19:02.666 --> 00:19:07.200
[Meeting Li Guinian in Jiangnan by Du Fu]
"I often saw you at Prince Qi's mansion

00:19:07.233 --> 00:19:13.233
and heard your music at Cui Jiu's home.

00:19:13.233 --> 00:19:18.633
This is just
when Jiangnan is at its finest,

00:19:18.633 --> 00:19:22.333
yet I meet you again as flowers fall."

00:19:22.400 --> 00:19:24.733
This poem by Du Fu is called

00:19:24.733 --> 00:19:28.033
"Meeting Li Guinian in Jiangnan".

00:19:28.066 --> 00:19:30.066
They were both written for Li Guinian.

00:19:31.266 --> 00:19:33.466
Which one do you prefer,

00:19:33.466 --> 00:19:35.366
this poem by Poet Sage Du Fu

00:19:35.400 --> 00:19:38.333
[Du Fu? Wang Wei?]
or the poem

00:19:38.333 --> 00:19:40.400
[Du Fu?]
by Poet Buddha Wang Wei?

00:19:40.433 --> 00:19:41.300
[Du Fu or Wang Wei]
Which one?

00:19:41.633 --> 00:19:43.433
[Du Fu or Wang Wei]

00:19:43.466 --> 00:19:44.766
Du Fu's.

00:19:44.800 --> 00:19:46.100
Any reason why?

00:19:46.100 --> 00:19:47.366
I think "Meeting" and "To"

00:19:47.400 --> 00:19:48.500
feel pretty different.

00:19:48.500 --> 00:19:49.433
[One word apart worlds apart]

00:19:50.133 --> 00:19:52.666
"Meeting Li Guinian" feels natural.

00:19:52.700 --> 00:19:53.333
Right.

00:19:53.333 --> 00:19:57.733
"To Mr. Li" sounds too formal.

00:19:57.733 --> 00:19:59.566
Okay, professor of etiquette.

00:19:59.733 --> 00:20:01.066
[Winning people with manners]

00:20:01.066 --> 00:20:02.800
No wonder when I gave you all

00:20:02.833 --> 00:20:04.300
a traditional fist-and-palm salute,

00:20:04.300 --> 00:20:06.133
you all laughed. Couldn't take it, huh?

00:20:06.133 --> 00:20:07.166
What about you?

00:20:07.200 --> 00:20:09.100
Personally, I prefer Wang Wei's.

00:20:09.100 --> 00:20:10.100
You prefer Wang Wei's.

00:20:10.100 --> 00:20:10.700
What about you?

00:20:10.700 --> 00:20:12.233
I prefer Du Fu's.

00:20:12.266 --> 00:20:12.766
Why?

00:20:12.800 --> 00:20:13.833
They like Wang Wei's.

00:20:13.833 --> 00:20:15.033
But you prefer Du Fu's.

00:20:17.933 --> 00:20:19.800
Because in his poems,

00:20:19.833 --> 00:20:21.833
Du Fu blends in his own experiences.

00:20:21.833 --> 00:20:22.366
He does.

00:20:23.233 --> 00:20:24.100
And his thoughts.

00:20:24.100 --> 00:20:25.800
While Wang Wei just describes things.

00:20:26.633 --> 00:20:27.466
[Nods silently]

00:20:27.500 --> 00:20:28.400
Who do you prefer?

00:20:28.433 --> 00:20:29.900
Wang Wei.

00:20:29.900 --> 00:20:30.700
Why?

00:20:30.700 --> 00:20:33.600
His poem is about yearning.

00:20:33.633 --> 00:20:35.466
You just like yearning, right?

00:20:39.466 --> 00:20:40.133
What about you?

00:20:40.533 --> 00:20:41.766
I'm into Wang Wei too.

00:20:41.800 --> 00:20:43.433
You like Wang Wei too? Why?

00:20:43.433 --> 00:20:44.633
Because I'm an intuitive type.

00:20:44.633 --> 00:20:45.466
What type are you?

00:20:45.466 --> 00:20:46.100
[Benefactor?]
[*Homophone]

00:20:47.633 --> 00:20:48.533
A feeling-driven person.

00:20:48.533 --> 00:20:48.866
What's it?

00:20:48.900 --> 00:20:50.133
The N in MBTI.

00:20:51.100 --> 00:20:52.566
That personality test, right?

00:20:52.600 --> 00:20:53.700
[This N isn't the benefactor.]
Right.

00:20:53.700 --> 00:20:54.500
Okay, benefactor.

00:20:54.500 --> 00:20:55.566
[Intuitive type]
I can't call you that.

00:20:55.833 --> 00:20:57.300
I don't know who you helped.

00:20:58.033 --> 00:20:59.033
What type are you?

00:20:59.033 --> 00:20:59.900
I'm an extrovert type.

00:20:59.900 --> 00:21:00.600
Extraverted type?

00:21:02.000 --> 00:21:03.033
You're ENFP.

00:21:03.033 --> 00:21:03.633
Intuitive type.

00:21:03.633 --> 00:21:05.566
I'm an intuitive type too.

00:21:05.600 --> 00:21:07.533
Who do you think Li Guinian likes?

00:21:07.533 --> 00:21:09.433
I honestly think he liked neither.

00:21:11.533 --> 00:21:13.133
Because if he liked either one,

00:21:13.133 --> 00:21:14.233
they would not need to write poems.

00:21:15.700 --> 00:21:16.600
You are not an intuitive type

00:21:16.633 --> 00:21:17.566
nor an extrovert type.

00:21:17.600 --> 00:21:18.433
You are a stubborn type.

00:21:18.433 --> 00:21:19.633
[Stubborn]

00:21:19.733 --> 00:21:20.633
Just kidding.

00:21:20.666 --> 00:21:23.133
[Serious answer]
I think he preferred Wang Wei.

00:21:23.133 --> 00:21:24.800
There is no record of Li Guinian

00:21:24.833 --> 00:21:26.900
commenting on their poems.

00:21:26.900 --> 00:21:28.566
But one Tang text,

00:21:28.600 --> 00:21:30.066
called Friends Talk in Yunxi,

00:21:30.933 --> 00:21:33.600
records that Li Guinian once,

00:21:33.633 --> 00:21:36.766
at a banquet
of the Central Hunan Provincial Inspector

00:21:36.800 --> 00:21:40.833
began by singing Wang Wei's Yearning.

00:21:42.000 --> 00:21:47.800
"I hope you will gather more."

00:21:47.800 --> 00:21:54.533
"For this is deepest yearning."

00:21:57.300 --> 00:22:01.533
After singing, Li Guinian wept,

00:22:02.466 --> 00:22:05.133
and died a few days later.

00:22:05.133 --> 00:22:07.600
But what is recorded

00:22:07.633 --> 00:22:09.833
isn't the tune he sang,

00:22:09.833 --> 00:22:12.366
but the direction he faced.

00:22:12.733 --> 00:22:14.433
[Thinking]

00:22:14.600 --> 00:22:16.266
Guess which way he was singing toward.

00:22:16.266 --> 00:22:17.566
South.

00:22:17.600 --> 00:22:18.533
Which south?

00:22:18.533 --> 00:22:19.733
Southeast or southwest?

00:22:19.733 --> 00:22:20.733
Southeast.

00:22:20.733 --> 00:22:21.733
Why southeast?

00:22:21.733 --> 00:22:23.133
Because you're from Shanghai?

00:22:23.133 --> 00:22:23.566
Right.

00:22:24.233 --> 00:22:25.533
He was singing to you.

00:22:25.533 --> 00:22:27.633
Who was from Chengdu again?

00:22:27.666 --> 00:22:29.300
Could he be singing to your hometown?

00:22:30.233 --> 00:22:31.933
Probably.

00:22:31.933 --> 00:22:33.633
He really was singing toward Chengdu.

00:22:33.666 --> 00:22:34.600
Not toward Shanghai.

00:22:35.000 --> 00:22:35.733
What a shame.

00:22:37.000 --> 00:22:38.100
Why is that?

00:22:38.100 --> 00:22:40.800
[Wild guess]
He yearns for someone southwest.

00:22:40.833 --> 00:22:42.966
The An Lushan Rebellion.

00:22:43.000 --> 00:22:44.500
Who fled to Chengdu?

00:22:45.633 --> 00:22:47.900
Emperor Xuanzong of Tang, Li Longji.

00:22:48.433 --> 00:22:49.366
[Learned something new]

00:22:49.400 --> 00:22:52.900
Let me ask about this line.

00:22:53.733 --> 00:22:56.800
I hope you will gather more.

00:22:56.833 --> 00:22:59.233
For this is the deepest yearning.

00:23:00.466 --> 00:23:02.366
So what is this yearning?

00:23:02.400 --> 00:23:03.333
The bond between kindred souls.

00:23:03.333 --> 00:23:04.033
The grace of being truly seen.

00:23:04.066 --> 00:23:05.500
A mutual understanding.

00:23:05.500 --> 00:23:07.566
Yes, it is the world's

00:23:08.500 --> 00:23:11.733
most beautiful feeling.

00:23:11.733 --> 00:23:16.333
It's what makes us human.

00:23:16.333 --> 00:23:20.133
At first, your heart aflutter.

00:23:20.133 --> 00:23:24.233
Later, yearning sinks to the bone.

00:23:24.266 --> 00:23:27.366
In the end, you're heartbroken.

00:23:28.633 --> 00:23:29.700
But if you've never loved,

00:23:30.733 --> 00:23:32.400
never cried, never laughed...

00:23:33.733 --> 00:23:36.600
how do we prove we lived?

00:23:43.133 --> 00:23:44.133
Class dismissed.

00:23:44.133 --> 00:23:45.166
Goodbye, sir.

00:23:46.400 --> 00:23:47.600
Goodbye, sir.

00:23:47.600 --> 00:23:48.400
Thank you, sir.

00:23:48.400 --> 00:23:49.033
Bye.

00:23:49.933 --> 00:23:51.166
[Next: Music Class]
Next up,

00:23:51.200 --> 00:23:53.233
let's hurry to the Music Room.

00:23:53.233 --> 00:23:53.966
Okay.

00:23:54.533 --> 00:23:56.566
[The music teacher is waiting.]

00:24:11.533 --> 00:24:13.666
[Heading to the Music Room.]

00:24:13.700 --> 00:24:14.300
I hear something.

00:24:14.900 --> 00:24:15.500
Right?

00:24:16.000 --> 00:24:17.633
[Today's music teacher]

00:24:20.800 --> 00:24:21.733
[Who did they see?]

00:24:34.333 --> 00:24:36.866
[Gina Alice, pianist]

00:24:36.966 --> 00:24:38.566
[Too stunned to speak]

00:24:38.633 --> 00:24:40.066
[Speechless]

00:24:46.733 --> 00:24:47.733
[Hello]

00:24:48.133 --> 00:24:48.933
That sounds amazing.

00:24:50.333 --> 00:24:52.833
Hi, everyone. I'm Gina Alice.

00:24:52.866 --> 00:24:55.266
Nice to meet you.

00:24:55.266 --> 00:24:56.800
I'm your music teacher.

00:24:56.833 --> 00:24:57.766
So beautiful.

00:24:57.800 --> 00:24:59.733
You all know each other well, right?

00:24:59.733 --> 00:25:01.233
[One new student]
I just got here today.

00:25:01.266 --> 00:25:01.900
Really?

00:25:01.900 --> 00:25:02.300
Yeah.

00:25:02.300 --> 00:25:04.200
Actually, we have one more student.

00:25:04.933 --> 00:25:06.266
[Another newcomer]

00:25:12.800 --> 00:25:13.666
And one more guest.

00:25:14.133 --> 00:25:14.866
A girl?

00:25:33.833 --> 00:25:37.233
[Olivia]

00:25:44.766 --> 00:25:45.866
[Peeks in]

00:25:45.900 --> 00:25:47.800
Let's welcome our new student.

00:25:47.833 --> 00:25:49.166
Hi, everyone.

00:25:50.333 --> 00:25:51.200
Hello, Ms. Alice.

00:25:52.133 --> 00:25:54.133
Hi, everyone. I'm Olivia.

00:25:54.600 --> 00:25:57.033
Olivia, like bright and graceful.

00:25:57.033 --> 00:25:58.533
Just call me Olivia.

00:25:58.533 --> 00:25:59.000
Olivia.

00:25:59.866 --> 00:26:00.500
Olivia.

00:26:01.600 --> 00:26:04.066
This is my good friend, Zhumi.

00:26:04.933 --> 00:26:06.266
[Zhumi]
Hi, everyone.

00:26:07.000 --> 00:26:08.233
[Totally charmed]
She's so cute.

00:26:08.233 --> 00:26:08.700
Oh my.

00:26:09.133 --> 00:26:10.133
She's really got something.

00:26:11.133 --> 00:26:13.766
Olivia is a very classic

00:26:13.800 --> 00:26:14.433
ENFP,

00:26:14.433 --> 00:26:15.333
"happy puppy" type.

00:26:16.200 --> 00:26:18.033
She's super forgetful,

00:26:18.033 --> 00:26:19.433
always leaving things behind.

00:26:20.866 --> 00:26:22.266
I told you not to say all that

00:26:22.266 --> 00:26:23.500
in front of beauties and handsomes.

00:26:23.600 --> 00:26:24.433
[Oops, wrong thing to say]

00:26:24.633 --> 00:26:27.566
[Mmm]

00:26:27.833 --> 00:26:28.900
[Starts clapping first]

00:26:32.933 --> 00:26:36.366
So I'm really excited for this trip.

00:26:36.400 --> 00:26:38.633
I'm so happy to meet you all.

00:26:38.633 --> 00:26:40.100
Last year,

00:26:40.100 --> 00:26:43.233
I came back after graduating
from Imperial College London.

00:26:43.266 --> 00:26:46.300
[Oh]
Before I start working,

00:26:46.300 --> 00:26:47.733
I want to give my student days

00:26:47.733 --> 00:26:49.433
a perfect ending.

00:26:50.100 --> 00:26:51.200
And I hope to meet

00:26:51.233 --> 00:26:53.966
a group of sweet, sincere people here,

00:26:54.000 --> 00:26:55.133
and go through things together

00:26:55.666 --> 00:26:57.366
that only youth

00:26:57.400 --> 00:26:59.033
can bring, adventures and sparks.

00:26:59.033 --> 00:27:00.233
So in the end,
I'm really looking forward

00:27:00.233 --> 00:27:02.033
to starting this

00:27:02.533 --> 00:27:04.733
wonderful, dreamy journey with you all.

00:27:04.733 --> 00:27:05.833
You got this, Zhumi.

00:27:05.866 --> 00:27:07.066
You got this, Olivia Zhu.

00:27:07.066 --> 00:27:07.933
Thank you, everyone.

00:27:09.333 --> 00:27:10.366
That was a great intro.

00:27:12.700 --> 00:27:14.133
So, who do you want to sit by?

00:27:14.700 --> 00:27:15.500
I'm good anywhere.

00:27:19.600 --> 00:27:21.233
How about I give you my seat?

00:27:27.100 --> 00:27:27.766
Come on.

00:27:27.800 --> 00:27:28.500
[Jack takes the initiative.]

00:27:28.500 --> 00:27:29.333
Come on.

00:27:29.333 --> 00:27:30.933
Okay, I'll sit there then.

00:27:30.933 --> 00:27:31.933
Okay.

00:27:31.933 --> 00:27:32.433
Come on.

00:27:32.466 --> 00:27:33.500
Okay, thanks.

00:27:33.500 --> 00:27:34.966
Same outfit. I got here today too.

00:27:35.000 --> 00:27:35.866
Hi.

00:27:35.866 --> 00:27:37.266
Hi, I'm Jack. Jack.

00:27:37.266 --> 00:27:37.766
Hi, Jack.

00:27:37.800 --> 00:27:38.233
Hi.

00:27:38.233 --> 00:27:39.666
Hi, I'm Olivia.

00:27:39.666 --> 00:27:40.866
Hi, I'm Jason.

00:27:40.866 --> 00:27:41.333
Jason?

00:27:41.333 --> 00:27:41.800
Yeah.

00:27:41.833 --> 00:27:42.033
Hi.

00:27:42.033 --> 00:27:42.866
I'm Olivia.

00:27:42.866 --> 00:27:44.866
Hi.

00:27:44.866 --> 00:27:45.366
Eon.

00:27:45.400 --> 00:27:46.833
Hi, Eon.

00:27:46.833 --> 00:27:47.766
Hi, I'm Hao Chen.

00:27:47.800 --> 00:27:48.100
Hao Chen.

00:27:48.100 --> 00:27:49.333
I study in the UK too.

00:27:49.866 --> 00:27:50.666
Hi.

00:27:51.100 --> 00:27:52.300
You can call me Yuna.

00:27:52.300 --> 00:27:53.033
It's easier to remember.

00:27:53.066 --> 00:27:53.566
Yuna.

00:27:53.600 --> 00:27:53.933
Yeah.

00:27:53.933 --> 00:27:55.066
Okay, thanks.

00:27:55.100 --> 00:27:56.333
I'm Zhaoyu Zhang.

00:27:56.333 --> 00:27:57.533
Zhaoyu, got it.

00:27:57.533 --> 00:27:58.800
You can call me Sean.

00:27:58.833 --> 00:27:59.700
Sean, Sean.

00:27:59.700 --> 00:28:01.366
Sean, okay. Hi.

00:28:01.400 --> 00:28:02.500
I'm Lily.

00:28:02.500 --> 00:28:03.733
You can call me Lily.

00:28:03.733 --> 00:28:04.833
Lily.

00:28:04.866 --> 00:28:05.600
I'm Nora.

00:28:05.633 --> 00:28:06.466
You can call me Nora.

00:28:06.466 --> 00:28:08.533
Hi, everyone.

00:28:09.066 --> 00:28:10.366
I'm really glad to meet you all.

00:28:14.233 --> 00:28:18.166
Today, our focus is singing together.

00:28:18.200 --> 00:28:19.700
The song we're doing today is

00:28:19.700 --> 00:28:21.766
Auld Lang Syne.

00:28:21.800 --> 00:28:24.466
I'll sing the German version for you.

00:28:24.466 --> 00:28:25.200
Applause.

00:28:27.166 --> 00:28:29.000
[Excited]

00:28:29.100 --> 00:28:33.766
[Auld Lang Syne German version]

00:28:54.800 --> 00:28:56.033
Bravo.

00:28:56.400 --> 00:28:57.066
Thank you.

00:28:58.066 --> 00:29:00.133
This song centers on

00:29:00.133 --> 00:29:01.433
the theme of saying goodbye.

00:29:01.466 --> 00:29:02.766
So I think today,

00:29:02.800 --> 00:29:06.600
let's really sing this one well.

00:29:06.600 --> 00:29:08.266
Next, we'll rehearse in pairs.

00:29:09.000 --> 00:29:10.066
Pair by pair.

00:29:10.833 --> 00:29:13.666
Is there anyone you like so far?

00:29:16.633 --> 00:29:17.566
Anyone at the moment?

00:29:21.100 --> 00:29:22.166
[Looks at Yuna]

00:29:23.000 --> 00:29:25.100
Who do you think you'd sound good

00:29:25.100 --> 00:29:25.933
singing with?

00:29:26.166 --> 00:29:26.800
Who would you click with?

00:29:27.300 --> 00:29:28.533
[Looks at Jason]

00:29:31.066 --> 00:29:32.933
Should we use Palm or Back of Hand?

00:29:32.933 --> 00:29:33.733
[Random teams]

00:29:33.733 --> 00:29:34.966
Come on.

00:29:35.000 --> 00:29:36.100
Hurry up, come on.

00:29:36.100 --> 00:29:37.433
Come on, go.

00:29:37.466 --> 00:29:38.333
Here we go.

00:29:38.333 --> 00:29:39.766
Palm or back.

00:29:41.033 --> 00:29:42.900
The four of us got back of hand.

00:29:42.900 --> 00:29:43.700
Why don't you choose?

00:29:43.700 --> 00:29:44.833
[Back of Hand]
You're the new classmate.

00:29:44.866 --> 00:29:47.066
My singing is pretty bad anyway.

00:29:47.066 --> 00:29:48.800
And you?

00:29:48.833 --> 00:29:49.566
It is actually okay.

00:29:49.600 --> 00:29:50.400
Then it's you.

00:29:50.400 --> 00:29:52.900
Let's make a beautiful melody together.

00:29:52.900 --> 00:29:53.533
Okay.

00:29:53.533 --> 00:29:54.566
[Teams: Hao Chen &amp; Olivia, Jason &amp; Lily]

00:29:54.800 --> 00:29:55.700
Come on, spin the phone.

00:29:56.800 --> 00:29:57.666
Then we're together.

00:29:57.666 --> 00:29:57.766
Okay.

00:29:57.800 --> 00:29:58.433
We're a team.

00:29:58.433 --> 00:29:59.166
[Team: Jack &amp; Yuna]

00:29:59.466 --> 00:30:01.100
[Team: Eon &amp; Zhaoyu Zhang]
What if I can't sing?

00:30:01.100 --> 00:30:02.433
I'll help you with it.

00:30:02.466 --> 00:30:03.300
Okay.

00:30:03.300 --> 00:30:04.900
I sing pretty badly.

00:30:04.900 --> 00:30:05.833
I'm counting on you.

00:30:05.866 --> 00:30:07.366
I'm not that great either.

00:30:07.900 --> 00:30:08.433
[Sean &amp; Nora.
Eon &amp; Zhaoyu]

00:30:08.433 --> 00:30:09.100
[Jack &amp; Yuna.
Hao Chen &amp; Olivia. Jason &amp; Lily]

00:30:09.133 --> 00:30:09.800
[Winter Class Committee]

00:30:10.133 --> 00:30:12.866
[Teaching starts]
You sing lines one and two.

00:30:12.900 --> 00:30:13.400
Okay.

00:30:13.433 --> 00:30:16.233
♪Should old acquaintance be forgot♪

00:30:16.233 --> 00:30:19.033
♪And never brought to mind?♪

00:30:19.033 --> 00:30:21.900
[Joins in]
♪Should old acquaintance be forgot♪

00:30:21.900 --> 00:30:24.633
♪And days of old long past♪

00:30:24.666 --> 00:30:25.266
Okay.

00:30:25.266 --> 00:30:26.266
Then let's sing this verse.

00:30:26.266 --> 00:30:26.566
Yes.

00:30:26.600 --> 00:30:27.300
We can do it.

00:30:27.666 --> 00:30:28.766
But we need to set the key.

00:30:28.800 --> 00:30:30.000
Or we can just start anywhere.

00:30:30.000 --> 00:30:31.500
If we start low, they'll sing low.

00:30:31.500 --> 00:30:33.133
I'll sing softly. You go louder.

00:30:33.133 --> 00:30:34.466
Okay.

00:30:34.500 --> 00:30:37.833
♪And we will take a cup of kindness yet♪

00:30:37.866 --> 00:30:40.800
♪For old long past♪

00:30:42.000 --> 00:30:44.433
[Group 3 lesson]
You sing verse one and two.

00:30:44.433 --> 00:30:48.133
♪Should old acquaintance be forgot♪

00:30:48.166 --> 00:30:48.566
Confident.

00:30:48.566 --> 00:30:52.300
♪And never brought to mind?♪

00:30:52.300 --> 00:30:56.533
[Look]
♪Should old acquaintance be forgot♪

00:30:56.533 --> 00:31:00.033
♪And days of old long past♪

00:31:00.066 --> 00:31:03.100
I think you can add more feeling.

00:31:03.100 --> 00:31:03.733
Okay, miss.

00:31:05.533 --> 00:31:06.233
Have you heard this song?

00:31:06.266 --> 00:31:06.966
I haven't.

00:31:07.700 --> 00:31:08.700
Okay.

00:31:08.700 --> 00:31:09.633
It's fine. We can do this.

00:31:10.733 --> 00:31:11.333
We can.

00:31:12.066 --> 00:31:12.666
Leave it to me.

00:31:13.266 --> 00:31:14.900
[Compliment mode on]
Pretty and nice.

00:31:14.900 --> 00:31:15.733
Alright, folk.

00:31:15.733 --> 00:31:16.600
Let's (rehearse).

00:31:20.633 --> 00:31:21.566
You two.

00:31:21.933 --> 00:31:25.033
[The prince starts singing.]

00:31:25.200 --> 00:31:28.666
[Nails it with ease]

00:31:29.100 --> 00:31:29.900
That feels so right.

00:31:30.500 --> 00:31:31.900
Thank you, miss.

00:31:31.900 --> 00:31:33.900
You're a postgrad
at Imperial College London?

00:31:34.433 --> 00:31:35.700
Yeah.

00:31:35.700 --> 00:31:36.300
What about you?

00:31:36.300 --> 00:31:37.933
I'm at the University of Cambridge.

00:31:38.366 --> 00:31:41.000
[University of Cambridge]

00:31:41.966 --> 00:31:42.966
That's amazing.

00:31:43.966 --> 00:31:46.566
[That's amazing]
I'm a first-year Ph.D. student.

00:31:47.033 --> 00:31:47.900
[So knowledgeable]

00:31:48.366 --> 00:31:49.500
[So impressive]
I'm flattered.

00:31:49.533 --> 00:31:51.466
♪Should old acquaintance be forgot♪

00:31:51.500 --> 00:31:54.000
[Last group lesson]
♪For old long past♪

00:31:54.500 --> 00:31:58.300
♪For old long past, my friend♪

00:31:58.366 --> 00:31:59.400
[Miss, how is it?]

00:31:59.400 --> 00:32:00.266
Right.

00:32:00.300 --> 00:32:00.600
Really?

00:32:00.633 --> 00:32:02.300
[Looks doubtful]

00:32:02.933 --> 00:32:04.666
Okay, let me hear it again.

00:32:04.700 --> 00:32:09.800
♪For old long past, my friend♪

00:32:09.800 --> 00:32:12.200
[Terrible]
♪And we will take a cup of kindness yet♪

00:32:12.200 --> 00:32:13.000
[Help me!]

00:32:14.733 --> 00:32:16.633
I couldn't hear your voice.

00:32:16.633 --> 00:32:18.566
I don't know the tune.

00:32:18.600 --> 00:32:20.400
Then just follow my lead.

00:32:21.000 --> 00:32:22.333
This is so funny.

00:32:22.366 --> 00:32:26.666
♪For old long past, my friend♪

00:32:27.000 --> 00:32:27.933
[No skills, all heart]

00:32:27.966 --> 00:32:31.466
♪And we will take a cup of kindness yet♪

00:32:33.233 --> 00:32:34.066
Let us help you out.

00:32:34.100 --> 00:32:35.833
We'll give you the starting note.

00:32:35.833 --> 00:32:36.533
Okay.

00:32:37.366 --> 00:32:39.866
Three, two, one.

00:32:39.900 --> 00:32:44.766
♪For old long past, my friend♪

00:32:44.766 --> 00:32:45.700
[Why did it go quiet?]

00:32:45.733 --> 00:32:49.633
♪For old long past♪

00:32:49.633 --> 00:32:50.733
[Quickly pulls it back]

00:32:50.933 --> 00:32:56.066
♪And we will take a cup of kindness yet♪

00:32:56.100 --> 00:33:00.166
♪For old long past♪

00:33:01.166 --> 00:33:02.200
Alright.

00:33:02.200 --> 00:33:04.400
I think I can back you up now.

00:33:07.133 --> 00:33:08.266
What an honor.

00:33:10.400 --> 00:33:12.000
I am so lucky.

00:33:12.000 --> 00:33:12.833
This is amazing.

00:33:13.233 --> 00:33:17.733
[Auld Lang Syne]

00:33:35.900 --> 00:33:41.400
♪Should old acquaintance be forgot♪

00:33:41.400 --> 00:33:46.466
♪And never brought to mind?♪

00:33:46.700 --> 00:33:51.566
♪Should old acquaintance be forgot♪

00:33:51.766 --> 00:33:56.800
♪And days of old long past♪

00:33:57.500 --> 00:34:02.733
♪We two have run about the hillsides♪

00:34:02.766 --> 00:34:07.400
♪And pulled the wild daisies fine♪

00:34:07.800 --> 00:34:12.566
♪But we have wandered many a weary foot♪

00:34:12.600 --> 00:34:13.500
I'm Zhaoyu Zhang.

00:34:13.533 --> 00:34:14.700
