00:40:10.766 --> 00:40:12.100
No, I mean...

00:40:12.400 --> 00:40:13.633
Sorry.

00:40:13.633 --> 00:40:14.333
Okay.

00:40:17.433 --> 00:40:18.833
What were you doing the other day?

00:40:19.966 --> 00:40:23.400
On day one, we met and performed.

00:40:23.400 --> 00:40:25.433
Yesterday, we split into pairs.

00:40:25.933 --> 00:40:27.200
Yuna and I were together.

00:40:28.000 --> 00:40:28.800
Do you think

00:40:29.900 --> 00:40:32.633
all four girls are easygoing?

00:40:32.633 --> 00:40:35.533
What stands out about them?

00:40:35.833 --> 00:40:36.733
[Testing the waters]

00:40:36.766 --> 00:40:37.566
What do you think?

00:40:38.166 --> 00:40:39.833
If I say too much, will I get...

00:40:40.833 --> 00:40:42.766
It's fine. Only I'll know.

00:40:44.133 --> 00:40:46.333
I think they're all great girls.

00:40:47.833 --> 00:40:49.866
Yuna is more...

00:40:49.900 --> 00:40:52.766
more cheerful, like sunshine.

00:40:52.766 --> 00:40:54.000
[Yuna: Cheerful, like sunshine]

00:40:54.000 --> 00:40:56.333
Nora has more personality.

00:40:57.233 --> 00:40:59.300
[Nora: Distinctive]
Zhaoyu Zhang is cheerful.

00:40:59.333 --> 00:41:01.000
[Zhaoyu Zhang: Cheerful]
Yeah, I see.

00:41:01.000 --> 00:41:02.733
Lily is a little more reserved.

00:41:02.766 --> 00:41:04.233
[Lily: Reserved]

00:41:04.233 --> 00:41:07.666
So, from the past few days together,

00:41:07.700 --> 00:41:09.766
does anyone seem more attractive

00:41:09.766 --> 00:41:10.433
to you?

00:41:10.433 --> 00:41:12.833
[Any guest you feel interested in?]

00:41:12.966 --> 00:41:14.900
It's fine. I'm just (curious).

00:41:19.966 --> 00:41:21.400
Personally,

00:41:21.400 --> 00:41:22.100
I'm more into

00:41:22.200 --> 00:41:24.866
[I'm more drawn to Yuna.]
Yuna.

00:41:26.233 --> 00:41:26.833
Because you know,

00:41:27.400 --> 00:41:28.266
I was teamed up with her yesterday,

00:41:28.600 --> 00:41:30.900
and we met each other first on day one.

00:41:30.933 --> 00:41:31.566
Yeah.

00:41:31.566 --> 00:41:32.300
Got it.

00:41:33.633 --> 00:41:35.366
Thanks for sharing your insight.

00:41:35.400 --> 00:41:36.066
You're welcome.

00:41:44.533 --> 00:41:45.966
[Looks around]

00:41:46.100 --> 00:41:47.500
[Nervously rubs hands]

00:41:51.033 --> 00:41:53.100
[Beaming]
Hi.

00:41:54.000 --> 00:41:56.633
Hello.

00:41:56.633 --> 00:41:57.266
Jack.

00:41:57.300 --> 00:41:58.433
[Lily arrives for the date.]

00:41:58.433 --> 00:42:00.033
What's my name?

00:42:00.033 --> 00:42:01.133
[Answers at once]
Lily.

00:42:01.166 --> 00:42:01.500
Okay.

00:42:01.533 --> 00:42:01.833
Right?

00:42:01.833 --> 00:42:03.633
So was it a Soul Match

00:42:03.633 --> 00:42:04.533
or did you invite me?

00:42:04.566 --> 00:42:06.566
I saw your profile

00:42:06.566 --> 00:42:08.400
[Hi, I hoped we'd meet on]
and then sent you an invite.

00:42:09.200 --> 00:42:10.733
[the third-floor corridor.]
Your Gravity Tags.

00:42:10.766 --> 00:42:12.066
[Their Gravity Tags]
"Planning Genius".

00:42:12.100 --> 00:42:13.166
"Always Have Headphones".

00:42:13.766 --> 00:42:15.433
[On the same wavelength]
Me too.

00:42:15.433 --> 00:42:16.233
[On the same wavelength]

00:42:16.333 --> 00:42:18.400
And you said you're an art student.

00:42:19.366 --> 00:42:21.033
So which school and major?

00:42:21.033 --> 00:42:22.566
I'm at Sichuan University,
majoring in fashion design.

00:42:23.333 --> 00:42:25.533
I really wanted fashion design too.

00:42:25.533 --> 00:42:27.133
Since I'm from Shanghai, Donghua...

00:42:27.133 --> 00:42:28.600
Donghua University? It's in my list too.

00:42:28.600 --> 00:42:29.866
But I missed it by a little.

00:42:30.533 --> 00:42:31.333
Me too.

00:42:31.333 --> 00:42:32.633
So you chose Jiangnan University?

00:42:32.633 --> 00:42:33.733
Yes. Jiangnan University.

00:42:33.766 --> 00:42:34.733
And I majored in product design.

00:42:35.166 --> 00:42:35.600
Yeah.

00:42:37.433 --> 00:42:38.433
You've got that trendy look.

00:42:39.400 --> 00:42:41.100
We girls all think so.

00:42:41.133 --> 00:42:42.233
Thank you.

00:42:42.233 --> 00:42:42.766
I'm flattered.

00:42:43.966 --> 00:42:45.466
[Softly praising]
You got great vibe.

00:42:45.500 --> 00:42:46.433
Thanks.

00:42:46.433 --> 00:42:47.433
[Trading compliments]
You're art students.

00:42:47.433 --> 00:42:49.033
We can spot each other's vibe.

00:42:49.500 --> 00:42:51.166
[Fashion detail]
Your outfit.

00:42:51.166 --> 00:42:52.566
The accessories as well.

00:42:52.800 --> 00:42:53.500
An art student.

00:42:55.733 --> 00:42:57.800
[Starting new topic]
I saw your skiing posts.

00:42:57.800 --> 00:42:58.933
So you really ski?

00:42:58.966 --> 00:43:00.966
Yeah, I really like skiing.

00:43:00.966 --> 00:43:02.500
Every winter,

00:43:02.533 --> 00:43:05.800
I hit different ski resorts.

00:43:05.800 --> 00:43:07.600
So do you snowboard?

00:43:07.600 --> 00:43:08.400
[Leans closer]
Yeah.

00:43:08.400 --> 00:43:09.266
Snowboard looks cooler.

00:43:09.766 --> 00:43:10.433
You know.

00:43:11.000 --> 00:43:12.500
Yeah, I saw your photos.

00:43:12.533 --> 00:43:14.133
And among us, you're probably the one

00:43:14.133 --> 00:43:15.266
[Keeps praising]
who's best at skiing.

00:43:15.700 --> 00:43:16.633
Really.

00:43:17.033 --> 00:43:18.366
A lot of people haven't learned yet,

00:43:18.400 --> 00:43:19.633
and some only took a few lessons.

00:43:19.633 --> 00:43:20.700
What about you?

00:43:20.733 --> 00:43:21.400
Me too, just a few lessons.

00:43:21.966 --> 00:43:23.366
It's fine. I'll teach you then.

00:43:23.366 --> 00:43:24.100
I'll teach you then.

00:43:24.700 --> 00:43:25.500
Okay.

00:43:26.766 --> 00:43:28.366
I did a lot of planning though.

00:43:28.366 --> 00:43:28.800
Nice.

00:43:28.800 --> 00:43:30.100
You feel me. We're both Type J.

00:43:30.133 --> 00:43:31.233
[One more thing in common]

00:43:31.233 --> 00:43:32.133
Exactly.

00:43:33.000 --> 00:43:35.600
So what do you usually do for fun?

00:43:36.566 --> 00:43:37.100
I

00:43:37.133 --> 00:43:37.466
like

00:43:37.500 --> 00:43:37.800
eating

00:43:37.800 --> 00:43:38.233
food.

00:43:39.600 --> 00:43:41.866
So why not eat and talk?

00:43:41.900 --> 00:43:43.000
[Finally remembered me]
Sure.

00:43:43.000 --> 00:43:43.800
Thanks.

00:43:43.800 --> 00:43:44.900
Let's see what we got today.

00:43:47.933 --> 00:43:49.366
Give it a try.

00:43:49.766 --> 00:43:51.566
I'm starving, seriously starving.

00:43:56.900 --> 00:43:57.600
I'm really excited.

00:43:58.800 --> 00:43:59.633
Seeing everyone...

00:44:04.166 --> 00:44:05.366
[With glasses on]

00:44:06.933 --> 00:44:07.933
It feels so different.

00:44:07.933 --> 00:44:08.833
Are you wearing glasses?

00:44:09.500 --> 00:44:10.166
I mean you.

00:44:11.366 --> 00:44:12.500
[Flustered and rambling]

00:44:12.700 --> 00:44:15.233
But we all thought you'd pick Yuna.

00:44:16.233 --> 00:44:17.500
Because it felt like

00:44:17.533 --> 00:44:19.000
the way you looked at her was different.

00:44:21.166 --> 00:44:22.833
Really?

00:44:22.833 --> 00:44:23.533
Because

00:44:24.566 --> 00:44:25.766
she and I from the same place.

00:44:25.766 --> 00:44:28.500
I feel like we'd have a lot to say.

00:44:28.533 --> 00:44:30.866
And after seeing your profile,

00:44:30.900 --> 00:44:31.733
I just felt

00:44:31.733 --> 00:44:33.133
I'd really like to talk about design.

00:44:33.133 --> 00:44:34.766
[I want to go deeper into that.]
Right.

00:44:37.600 --> 00:44:38.433
Right.

00:44:42.900 --> 00:44:44.600
[Holds breath]

00:44:47.366 --> 00:44:48.633
[Watching]

00:44:49.533 --> 00:44:50.533
Are you nervous?

00:44:51.633 --> 00:44:52.166
I'm okay.

00:44:52.200 --> 00:44:52.733
Really?

00:44:52.766 --> 00:44:53.433
I'm okay.

00:44:54.133 --> 00:44:56.166
Maybe I'm excited, and...

00:44:56.300 --> 00:44:57.500
[You know what I mean]

00:44:58.033 --> 00:44:59.633
I'm the kind of person who really

00:44:59.633 --> 00:45:01.433
likes meeting new people.

00:45:01.433 --> 00:45:03.466
Yeah, and I really like

00:45:03.500 --> 00:45:05.033
hanging out with everyone, yeah.

00:45:10.000 --> 00:45:10.700
[Following]

00:45:10.733 --> 00:45:12.533
Don't sigh. Relax a little.

00:45:13.533 --> 00:45:14.800
Do you get anxious easily?

00:45:15.633 --> 00:45:16.700
Honestly, maybe I do.

00:45:16.733 --> 00:45:18.333
[One more thing in common]
I do too.

00:45:18.333 --> 00:45:20.000
I get really anxious.

00:45:25.433 --> 00:45:30.166
[So when you're free,
do you shop with friends?]

00:45:30.566 --> 00:45:32.300
Rarely. I actually like shopping alone.

00:45:32.400 --> 00:45:34.500
[I totally feel you.]

00:45:34.566 --> 00:45:37.766
That's basically
how I am in Shanghai too,

00:45:37.766 --> 00:45:38.633
on my own.

00:45:38.633 --> 00:45:39.500
By yourself, right?

00:45:39.533 --> 00:45:39.733
Right.

00:45:39.733 --> 00:45:41.200
Actually, I really like being alone.

00:45:41.200 --> 00:45:41.800
I didn't before,

00:45:41.800 --> 00:45:42.800
but now I do.

00:45:42.800 --> 00:45:44.200
Doing things on my own.

00:45:44.200 --> 00:45:45.933
Like shopping, or...

00:45:45.966 --> 00:45:47.766
sometimes I even like eating alone.

00:45:50.400 --> 00:45:52.066
Isn't there that loneliness scale?

00:45:53.333 --> 00:45:55.400
I'm not that lonely, really.

00:45:55.400 --> 00:45:56.600
Eating alone?

00:45:56.600 --> 00:45:57.666
Going to the movies alone?

00:45:57.700 --> 00:45:59.200
Going to a concert alone?

00:45:59.200 --> 00:45:59.800
I've done all that.

00:45:59.800 --> 00:46:00.500
Me too, all of it.

00:46:00.533 --> 00:46:01.833
Well, except the movies, maybe.

00:46:01.833 --> 00:46:02.633
I've never done that alone.

00:46:02.633 --> 00:46:03.366
Okay.

00:46:05.566 --> 00:46:07.900
I really love food, and...

00:46:07.933 --> 00:46:08.633
You never gain weight.

00:46:09.600 --> 00:46:10.266
Same here.

00:46:10.300 --> 00:46:11.233
We're so alike.

00:46:11.233 --> 00:46:11.966
Seriously, so alike.

00:46:52.200 --> 00:46:53.233
What's going on here?

00:46:53.966 --> 00:46:56.033
[Seats facing each other in pairs]

00:46:56.366 --> 00:46:57.633
One, two, three, four, five, six.

00:46:57.633 --> 00:46:58.333
How many are we now?

00:46:58.366 --> 00:47:00.300
One, two, three, four, five, six.

00:47:00.333 --> 00:47:01.666
These seats face each other.

00:47:01.700 --> 00:47:03.566
[Hesitates]
This is really something.

00:47:03.566 --> 00:47:05.900
[Zhaoyu Zhang]
Come on, face me.

00:47:05.933 --> 00:47:07.000
[Directly chooses Eon]
Let's eat face-to-face.

00:47:07.000 --> 00:47:07.500
Okay.

00:47:07.533 --> 00:47:08.033
Let's do it.

00:47:08.033 --> 00:47:08.866
[Actively invites Nora]
Then we can...

00:47:08.900 --> 00:47:09.533
Come on.

00:47:10.133 --> 00:47:11.166
This is really something.

00:47:13.766 --> 00:47:14.500
[Discovers something]

00:47:14.533 --> 00:47:16.033
Guys, want a drink or not?

00:47:16.166 --> 00:47:17.100
[Ten cups of drinks appear mysteriously]

00:47:17.133 --> 00:47:18.000
Milk tea?

00:47:18.000 --> 00:47:18.733
Coffee, I guess.

00:47:20.700 --> 00:47:21.766
It really is milk tea.

00:47:21.766 --> 00:47:22.833
Really?

00:47:22.833 --> 00:47:23.300
Seriously?

00:47:23.566 --> 00:47:23.966
Yeah.

00:47:23.966 --> 00:47:25.066
It really is milk tea.

00:47:25.100 --> 00:47:26.300
Taro-flavored milk tea!

00:47:26.300 --> 00:47:27.566
[Surprised]
Taro-flavored milk tea!

00:47:29.166 --> 00:47:30.366
It was the wish I made yesterday.

00:47:30.366 --> 00:47:31.466
No way, really?

00:47:33.833 --> 00:47:36.533
[Yuna's wish: Hope to drink
taro milk tea this winter]

00:47:36.633 --> 00:47:37.500
[Magic Lamp wish granted 1/8]

00:47:37.533 --> 00:47:39.233
I didn't expect it this fast.

00:47:40.000 --> 00:47:41.933
[Keeps eating quietly]

00:47:42.500 --> 00:47:44.366
This looks like those
Northeastern boxed meals, right?

00:47:45.233 --> 00:47:47.066
Like Northeastern boxed meals.

00:47:47.100 --> 00:47:48.333
I've never eaten
Northeastern boxed meals.

00:47:49.500 --> 00:47:50.200
What do people eat there?

00:47:50.200 --> 00:47:50.900
Sweet and sour pork.

00:47:51.766 --> 00:47:53.100
Do you usually cook?

00:47:53.133 --> 00:47:54.066
Yeah, I do.

00:47:54.100 --> 00:47:55.233
What can you make?

00:47:55.233 --> 00:47:56.966
Steak fried with
Master Kong Braised Beef Noodles.

00:47:57.000 --> 00:47:57.933
What is that?

00:47:58.333 --> 00:48:01.033
[Steak fried with
Master Kong Braised Beef Noodles]

00:48:01.033 --> 00:48:01.900
That sounds terrifying.

00:48:01.933 --> 00:48:04.600
I can make fried eggs with shizi.

00:48:04.600 --> 00:48:05.300
Eggs fried with what?

00:48:05.766 --> 00:48:06.633
Eggs fried with shizi.

00:48:06.633 --> 00:48:07.433
How do you even eat that?

00:48:07.433 --> 00:48:08.300
Eggs fried with shizi?

00:48:08.333 --> 00:48:09.433
Eggs fried with...

00:48:09.433 --> 00:48:10.733
Tomato fried with tomato.

00:48:11.800 --> 00:48:13.133
No, tomato fried with eggs.

00:48:14.000 --> 00:48:15.066
No, wait.

00:48:15.100 --> 00:48:16.000
Tomato is tomato.

00:48:16.000 --> 00:48:16.933
Shizi is the persimmon.

00:48:16.966 --> 00:48:18.266
Shizi is the tomato.

00:48:18.300 --> 00:48:19.500
[Two kids arguing about persimmons]
Shizi is the persimmon.

00:48:19.500 --> 00:48:21.100
Shizi is the tomato.

00:48:21.100 --> 00:48:22.000
[Everyone, judge this]
Is shizi the persimmon?

00:48:22.000 --> 00:48:23.300
Or is shizi the tomato?

00:48:23.333 --> 00:48:24.666
[Jason teammate +1]
Shizi is the persimmon.

00:48:24.700 --> 00:48:25.700
[Nora teammate +1]
Shizi is the tomato.

00:48:25.700 --> 00:48:26.166
Right.

00:48:26.166 --> 00:48:27.433
[Jason teammate +2]
Foreign Shizi is the tomato.

00:48:27.433 --> 00:48:28.500
Shizi is the tomato.

00:48:28.533 --> 00:48:28.933
Shizi is the persimmon.

00:48:28.933 --> 00:48:30.833
Foreign Shizi is the tomato.

00:48:30.833 --> 00:48:32.566
[Help needed]
Then what's xihongshi?

00:48:32.600 --> 00:48:33.666
Xihongshi is the tomato.

00:48:33.700 --> 00:48:34.900
Then what is shizi?

00:48:34.900 --> 00:48:36.300
Shizi is the persimmon.

00:48:36.300 --> 00:48:38.333
[Soul question: What variety is xihongshi?]
No, what variety is xihongshi?

00:48:38.333 --> 00:48:40.366
Doesn't it count as the shizi variety?

00:48:40.366 --> 00:48:41.266
No way!

00:48:41.300 --> 00:48:42.566
[#Is xihongshi really shizi?#]
Shizi is the persimmon.

00:48:42.566 --> 00:48:43.633
Shizi is a fruit.

00:48:43.633 --> 00:48:44.566
A fruit, right?

00:48:44.600 --> 00:48:45.666
The yellow one.

00:48:45.700 --> 00:48:47.233
No.

00:48:47.233 --> 00:48:48.700
I can't win against them, okay?

00:48:48.733 --> 00:48:51.266
There were three of them on me.

00:48:51.300 --> 00:48:52.366
I'm really speechless with you.

00:48:54.966 --> 00:48:55.566
After we got back yesterday,

00:48:56.566 --> 00:48:59.700
I went to Sean and Eon again.

00:49:00.500 --> 00:49:01.766
You guys still chatted?

00:49:01.766 --> 00:49:02.966
The three of us just
stared around.

00:49:03.200 --> 00:49:04.733
[Awkward]

00:49:04.766 --> 00:49:05.966
Why stare?

00:49:05.966 --> 00:49:06.400
What did you talk about?

00:49:06.400 --> 00:49:08.133
I said we three all
chose the same person.

00:49:09.000 --> 00:49:09.633
Yes.

00:49:11.133 --> 00:49:12.366
Then only Eon didn't know

00:49:14.000 --> 00:49:15.333
because he didn't know
what pickled fish stood for.

00:49:17.200 --> 00:49:18.233
I felt he was always confused.

00:49:18.233 --> 00:49:19.166
But he's really funny.

00:49:19.766 --> 00:49:22.000
He really does have his charm.

00:49:23.533 --> 00:49:24.433
The same goes for you.

00:49:24.633 --> 00:49:25.666
[Same goes for you]

00:49:25.733 --> 00:49:27.166
[Happy again]

00:49:27.833 --> 00:49:28.833
[You too]

00:49:28.833 --> 00:49:29.666
[Of course]

00:49:31.366 --> 00:49:32.700
I've got strong self-worth.

00:49:32.733 --> 00:49:33.433
Okay.

00:49:34.633 --> 00:49:35.666
Cheers.

00:49:38.833 --> 00:49:39.733
Dream came true.

00:49:39.766 --> 00:49:40.433
Let's take a photo.

00:49:44.000 --> 00:49:45.100
Can't get a good shot, backlit.

00:49:47.733 --> 00:49:48.600
Let me see.

00:49:56.733 --> 00:49:57.366
Not bad.

00:49:59.600 --> 00:50:01.000
What are they doing? Taking selfies?

00:50:01.000 --> 00:50:03.266
Taking close-ups of the cups.

00:50:03.300 --> 00:50:05.200
[Helps focus]
Such a niche hobby.

00:50:05.233 --> 00:50:08.100
[Photographer Hao Chen, out of focus]

00:50:08.366 --> 00:50:10.966
[Feels like opening blind boxes every day.
And each one is a happy surprise]

00:50:10.966 --> 00:50:12.066
Yeah.

00:50:12.100 --> 00:50:13.366
I'm full.

00:50:13.366 --> 00:50:14.400
That was fast.

00:50:16.800 --> 00:50:17.733
[Sneaks a glance]

00:50:20.200 --> 00:50:21.900
Look out the window, okay?

00:50:23.400 --> 00:50:24.200
Why look out the window?

00:50:24.633 --> 00:50:25.366
[Stares]

00:50:25.566 --> 00:50:26.266
Eat more veggies.

00:50:27.633 --> 00:50:29.466
Are you supervising my eating now?

00:50:29.500 --> 00:50:30.600
This is so weird.

00:50:30.600 --> 00:50:31.833
Can't you do your own thing?

00:50:31.833 --> 00:50:32.533
Eat more veggies.

00:50:34.366 --> 00:50:36.633
Let's see how much you can waste.

00:50:39.600 --> 00:50:40.500
"Are you crazy?"

00:50:41.833 --> 00:50:43.633
Let's play that hand-slapping game.

00:50:43.633 --> 00:50:44.266
Come on.

00:50:44.300 --> 00:50:45.233
You say, "Three, two, one, go."

00:50:45.233 --> 00:50:46.833
Okay. Three, two, one.

00:50:46.833 --> 00:50:48.033
You didn't say "go" yet.

00:50:48.033 --> 00:50:49.100
I did. Three, two, one.

00:50:49.133 --> 00:50:50.833
You have to say, "Three, two, one, go."

00:50:50.833 --> 00:50:51.966
I didn't say "go".

00:50:52.000 --> 00:50:53.266
Then let me slap you once.

00:50:53.300 --> 00:50:54.766
Fine, again.

00:50:54.766 --> 00:50:56.000
Three, two, one, go.

00:50:56.000 --> 00:50:56.633
Go.

00:51:00.566 --> 00:51:01.466
Three, two, one.

00:51:03.133 --> 00:51:03.866
You...

00:51:03.900 --> 00:51:04.533
Go.

00:51:05.833 --> 00:51:07.333
Who plays like that?

00:51:07.366 --> 00:51:09.033
You can't cheat.

00:51:09.033 --> 00:51:10.033
I wasn't cheating.

00:51:10.033 --> 00:51:10.900
You're just playing dirty.

00:51:10.933 --> 00:51:12.966
Okay, three, two, one, go.

00:51:20.033 --> 00:51:21.933
[Overly forceful]

00:51:22.400 --> 00:51:23.300
Come on.

00:51:23.333 --> 00:51:24.666
You've touched my reverse scale.

00:51:25.900 --> 00:51:26.566
Come on.

00:51:30.500 --> 00:51:31.233
I'm done playing.

00:51:31.233 --> 00:51:31.833
I'm done playing!

00:51:31.833 --> 00:51:32.733
Play by yourself.

00:51:32.766 --> 00:51:33.633
This is boring.

00:51:33.633 --> 00:51:34.333
I'm done playing.

00:51:34.366 --> 00:51:36.066
This game isn't fun with you.

00:51:40.400 --> 00:51:41.100
I'm full.

00:51:43.733 --> 00:51:45.833
[Post-meal zoning out]

00:51:45.833 --> 00:51:46.966
[Initiates conversation]
So, what did you do in college?

00:51:48.633 --> 00:51:49.666
College?

00:51:52.200 --> 00:51:53.333
[Studied]

00:51:53.366 --> 00:51:54.033
Besides that?

00:51:54.033 --> 00:51:55.866
[Curious]

00:51:56.533 --> 00:51:57.700
Learned some...

00:51:57.966 --> 00:51:59.900
[Economics and finance knowledge]

00:51:59.966 --> 00:52:01.233
[Straight up]
You had no entertainment life?

00:52:01.233 --> 00:52:02.733
Entertainment life? Of course, I did.

00:52:03.233 --> 00:52:03.966
I mean that kind...

00:52:04.000 --> 00:52:04.800
Playing games.

00:52:05.200 --> 00:52:05.900
Alright.

00:52:11.333 --> 00:52:12.566
[Mutually boring]

00:52:12.900 --> 00:52:13.566
I'm so sleepy.

00:52:14.700 --> 00:52:15.500
When I got up this morning,

00:52:15.500 --> 00:52:17.900
I couldn't even put my lenses in.

00:52:17.900 --> 00:52:18.333
And then...

00:52:18.333 --> 00:52:19.166
Were your eyes swollen?

00:52:19.166 --> 00:52:19.433
No,

00:52:19.433 --> 00:52:20.666
my eyes just hurt.

00:52:20.700 --> 00:52:21.766
And by the end...

00:52:21.766 --> 00:52:23.233
[Concerned]
How strong are your contacts?

00:52:23.233 --> 00:52:23.966
550 degrees.

00:52:24.000 --> 00:52:25.500
550 degrees with contacts?

00:52:25.533 --> 00:52:26.533
That's a bit...

00:52:27.133 --> 00:52:27.766
[Thick]
If I were...

00:52:27.766 --> 00:52:28.466
No.

00:52:29.166 --> 00:52:30.800
You're so funny.

00:52:30.800 --> 00:52:33.433
Let me tell you a quick science fact.

00:52:33.433 --> 00:52:35.400
Journey to Science.

00:52:35.433 --> 00:52:38.100
"The Secret of Contact Lenses".

00:52:38.133 --> 00:52:39.400
That only applies to framed ones.

00:52:39.400 --> 00:52:40.333
[Today's topic: Are higher-degree
contact lenses thicker?]

00:52:40.366 --> 00:52:43.766
Higher degrees make the lenses thicker.

00:52:43.766 --> 00:52:45.800
But for contact lenses,

00:52:45.800 --> 00:52:47.800
they only vary by prescription.

00:52:47.800 --> 00:52:48.400
Okay.

00:52:48.400 --> 00:52:50.133
The thickness stays

00:52:50.166 --> 00:52:51.000
the same.

00:52:51.400 --> 00:52:53.266
[Got it]

00:52:54.000 --> 00:52:54.866
You're too funny.

00:52:56.633 --> 00:52:57.033
Haven't you noticed...?

00:52:57.033 --> 00:52:58.866
You've had this hairstyle for days.

00:53:01.000 --> 00:53:01.866
Is that real?

00:53:01.900 --> 00:53:02.533
No way.

00:53:02.533 --> 00:53:03.566
This is a new hairstyle today.

00:53:03.566 --> 00:53:05.166
[Let me test you.
Happy examiner: Zhaoyu Zhang]

00:53:05.600 --> 00:53:06.433
What hairstyle did I have yesterday?

00:53:07.300 --> 00:53:08.100
Yesterday?

00:53:08.100 --> 00:53:15.433
[Q: What hairstyle did Zhaoyu Zhang have yesterday?
A. Twin tails. B. Twin buns. C. Single side bun. D. Single ponytail.]

00:53:15.433 --> 00:53:16.300
Give me a hint.

00:53:17.033 --> 00:53:18.466
I wore a star yesterday.

00:53:18.500 --> 00:53:20.033
[I will remove one wrong answer for you]

00:53:21.166 --> 00:53:24.000
From this angle, it looks like two buns.

00:53:24.000 --> 00:53:24.833
[Outside help]
Stop messing around.

00:53:24.833 --> 00:53:26.166
Come on, think carefully.

00:53:26.200 --> 00:53:27.200
She was not like that yesterday.

00:53:27.200 --> 00:53:28.333
She had that on the first day.

00:53:33.166 --> 00:53:34.033
Why do I feel like...?

00:53:34.300 --> 00:53:35.733
[Completely forgot]

00:53:36.433 --> 00:53:38.433
Let me check your photo.

00:53:38.433 --> 00:53:39.433
This is too funny.

00:53:39.433 --> 00:53:40.700
Did we take a photo together yesterday?

00:53:41.333 --> 00:53:42.266
Let me check what you posted.

00:53:45.033 --> 00:53:46.500
So this...

00:53:46.533 --> 00:53:47.366
[Technical term]
What's the technical term called?

00:53:48.233 --> 00:53:48.866
I don't know.

00:53:50.333 --> 00:53:52.000
Maybe like a side bun.

00:53:52.000 --> 00:53:53.900
A side bun plus a star, and hair down.

00:53:54.833 --> 00:53:55.966
[First time getting Zhaoyu Zhang]
Then this is two buns.

00:53:56.000 --> 00:53:57.866
Like two sticking out like this.

00:53:57.900 --> 00:53:59.233
Plus two hair clips.

00:53:59.766 --> 00:54:01.600
[Okay]

00:54:03.633 --> 00:54:06.300
[Looking at the photo closely]

00:54:06.633 --> 00:54:07.933
These are way too funny.

00:54:09.000 --> 00:54:09.600
I'm so sleepy.

00:54:10.400 --> 00:54:11.100
So sleepy.

00:54:13.966 --> 00:54:15.300
[Glances]

00:54:15.633 --> 00:54:16.333
Go to sleep.

00:54:17.600 --> 00:54:18.266
Let's both sleep.

00:54:20.500 --> 00:54:21.200
Sleep face down.

00:54:23.133 --> 00:54:23.800
Wake up, hurry.

00:54:24.766 --> 00:54:26.666
Drinking milk tea makes you sleepier.

00:54:27.433 --> 00:54:29.100
We should drink less sweet stuff.

00:54:29.133 --> 00:54:29.800
Yeah.

00:54:38.833 --> 00:54:40.266
Hello, you're back.

00:54:41.100 --> 00:54:42.233
[Jack and Lily return from lunch]
Do you want to sit here?

00:54:42.233 --> 00:54:42.900
Sure.

00:54:42.933 --> 00:54:43.566
Closer to me.

00:54:46.966 --> 00:54:49.600
[Olivia and Sean return too]

00:54:56.766 --> 00:54:59.033
Isn't anyone curious

00:54:59.033 --> 00:55:01.133
where this milk tea came from?

00:55:01.433 --> 00:55:04.566
[Where did the milk tea come from?]

00:55:04.600 --> 00:55:06.666
I made it for everyone myself.

00:55:06.700 --> 00:55:07.566
Really?

00:55:07.566 --> 00:55:10.500
Because I received this note.

00:55:10.533 --> 00:55:13.600
It said someone's wish.

00:55:14.700 --> 00:55:18.100
She said she wanted
to drink taro-flavored milk tea.

00:55:18.100 --> 00:55:19.500
[Gets it instantly]

00:55:19.566 --> 00:55:20.600
Guess whose it was.

00:55:20.600 --> 00:55:21.466
Guess whose wish it was.

00:55:22.533 --> 00:55:24.333
[Yours]

00:55:24.366 --> 00:55:25.666
How did you know?

00:55:25.700 --> 00:55:27.500
Because your reaction
to me was very strong.

00:55:30.533 --> 00:55:31.333
Thanks.

00:55:31.966 --> 00:55:33.100
Your wish came true.

00:55:33.133 --> 00:55:33.766
Magic!

00:55:34.600 --> 00:55:36.133
So sweet.

00:55:36.166 --> 00:55:37.766
[The first wish came true]

00:55:41.166 --> 00:55:41.966
Go on, drink up.

00:55:41.966 --> 00:55:43.700
Take your seats, I'll sit too.

00:55:43.733 --> 00:55:45.166
[Twinkle Love in Winter]

00:55:45.166 --> 00:55:46.266
Hello, everyone.

00:55:46.766 --> 00:55:47.266
Hello, teacher.

00:55:47.300 --> 00:55:47.766
Hello, teacher!

00:55:47.766 --> 00:55:49.466
You all seem really happy now.

00:55:49.500 --> 00:55:51.733
Did you learn a lot in class?

00:55:52.333 --> 00:55:54.633
After all that focused learning,

00:55:54.633 --> 00:55:58.033
it's time for fun club activities.

00:55:58.766 --> 00:56:01.466
So I thought,
let's have a Badminton Club.

00:56:01.966 --> 00:56:03.366
Since that's an active one,

00:56:03.366 --> 00:56:04.500
we should have a quiet one too.

00:56:04.533 --> 00:56:06.766
Let's have a Sketching Club too.

00:56:06.766 --> 00:56:07.233
How does that sound?

00:56:07.233 --> 00:56:07.966
[Afternoon club activities:
Badminton Club, Sketching Club]

00:56:08.000 --> 00:56:08.533
Okay.

00:56:08.566 --> 00:56:09.500
Next up,

00:56:09.533 --> 00:56:12.733
is there any student willing
to be the club president?

00:56:12.733 --> 00:56:13.733
Feel free to volunteer

00:56:13.733 --> 00:56:15.466
or nominate each other.

00:56:15.500 --> 00:56:16.633
Will you be the club president?

00:56:16.633 --> 00:56:17.166
[Encouraging]

00:56:18.500 --> 00:56:19.100
For drawing?

00:56:19.200 --> 00:56:20.133
[Raises hand right away]

00:56:20.166 --> 00:56:20.900
Okay, come on.

00:56:20.933 --> 00:56:22.266
Come stand up here.

00:56:22.300 --> 00:56:24.333
And the Badminton Club, too.

00:56:24.333 --> 00:56:25.333
Do we even need to guess?

00:56:25.333 --> 00:56:26.733
He brought his OOTD.

00:56:27.200 --> 00:56:29.333
[Came equipped]

00:56:29.533 --> 00:56:32.200
[Badminton President, Sketching President]
Great, our two presidents are selected.

00:56:32.200 --> 00:56:34.266
Next, we need members

00:56:34.300 --> 00:56:36.333
to join these two clubs.

00:56:36.566 --> 00:56:38.500
Who wants to join the Sketching Club?

00:56:38.766 --> 00:56:39.900
[Expectant]

00:56:41.400 --> 00:56:42.466
[Hinting]

00:56:42.633 --> 00:56:43.633
[Raises hand first]

00:56:44.766 --> 00:56:47.100
You two raised hands quickly.

00:56:47.733 --> 00:56:48.400
Come on, over here.

00:56:48.533 --> 00:56:50.433
[Olivia joins the Sketching Club]

00:56:51.533 --> 00:56:52.466
[Lily joins the Sketching Club]

00:56:52.500 --> 00:56:52.800
Okay.

00:56:53.100 --> 00:56:55.633
We still need two more.

00:56:56.300 --> 00:56:58.733
[Signal sent]

00:56:58.733 --> 00:56:59.633
[Signal received]

00:56:59.633 --> 00:57:02.933
[Quietly observing]

00:57:05.700 --> 00:57:06.966
Do you really want to join?

00:57:07.400 --> 00:57:08.700
Yes, teacher.

00:57:08.733 --> 00:57:09.600
Okay, I'll give you a shot.

00:57:10.133 --> 00:57:11.000
[Yuna joins the Sketching Club]
Thanks, teacher.

00:57:11.000 --> 00:57:12.733
The Sketching Club needs one more.

00:57:12.933 --> 00:57:14.733
[One spot left in Sketching Club]

00:57:18.400 --> 00:57:19.933
This group needs one more then.

00:57:21.000 --> 00:57:22.100
I'll go.

00:57:22.133 --> 00:57:22.866
[Raises hand first]
I'll go.

00:57:22.900 --> 00:57:23.300
Great.

00:57:23.300 --> 00:57:23.800
Okay.

00:57:23.800 --> 00:57:24.533
Good, formed.

00:57:27.400 --> 00:57:29.933
Our Sketching Club is full.

00:57:29.966 --> 00:57:31.066
As for the rest of you,

00:57:31.100 --> 00:57:33.500
you'll join the Badminton Club.

00:57:34.833 --> 00:57:36.533
[Club Activities: Sketching Club.
Jack, Olivia, Lily, Yuna, Sean]

00:57:36.566 --> 00:57:38.366
[Badminton Club.
Hao Chen, Nora, Jason, Zhaoyu Zhang, Eon]

00:57:38.900 --> 00:57:40.633
Welcome to the Sketching Club.

00:57:40.633 --> 00:57:42.333
How about this? Everyone take a paper.

00:57:42.366 --> 00:57:44.066
Then I'll pick a theme.

00:57:44.100 --> 00:57:45.900
And everyone draws one thing.

00:57:45.900 --> 00:57:47.166
Let's start with animals.

00:57:47.166 --> 00:57:47.433
Sure.

00:57:47.433 --> 00:57:48.066
Draw animals.

00:57:48.100 --> 00:57:48.600
Starting with animals.

00:57:48.600 --> 00:57:49.033
Okay.

00:57:49.033 --> 00:57:49.866
Good.

00:57:49.900 --> 00:57:50.600
Okay.

00:57:50.600 --> 00:57:52.533
[Focused]

00:57:56.500 --> 00:57:57.833
This one looks really good.

00:57:58.933 --> 00:57:59.733
That's impressive.

00:57:59.733 --> 00:58:01.400
No need to force it.

00:58:05.600 --> 00:58:06.700
Does the technique look familiar?

00:58:08.100 --> 00:58:09.433
Show us your pro skills.

00:58:10.600 --> 00:58:11.833
I'm really bad with color.

00:58:13.166 --> 00:58:14.500
Then I'm really good at it.

00:58:14.533 --> 00:58:14.966
Really?

00:58:14.966 --> 00:58:15.666
Yes.

00:58:18.366 --> 00:58:19.433
It's okay.

00:58:19.433 --> 00:58:20.066
Just put it here.

00:58:20.100 --> 00:58:21.033
Okay.

00:58:21.033 --> 00:58:21.533
Good.

00:58:21.566 --> 00:58:23.366
Feels like training camp again.

00:58:23.800 --> 00:58:24.433
Yeah.

00:58:27.800 --> 00:58:28.866
Teacher, can I ask something?

00:58:28.900 --> 00:58:31.633
Is talent for painting inborn,

00:58:31.633 --> 00:58:33.733
or can it be developed later?

00:58:33.766 --> 00:58:36.666
Everyone has a different style.

00:58:37.633 --> 00:58:39.833
What each person paints has charm.

00:58:39.833 --> 00:58:42.166
Like Picasso once said,

00:58:42.200 --> 00:58:43.633
[I spent four years painting like Raphael.]
he spent his whole life chasing

00:58:43.633 --> 00:58:45.233
[But it takes a lifetime to paint like a child. -Picasso]
painting like a child.

00:58:46.733 --> 00:58:48.133
[He spent his whole life chasing painting like a child. -Jack]
He spent his whole life chasing

00:58:48.433 --> 00:58:50.166
painting like a child.

00:58:50.200 --> 00:58:51.433
That makes sense.

00:58:51.433 --> 00:58:52.433
[Got it]
That is so profound.

00:58:54.333 --> 00:58:55.733
[Olivia finished first]
Teacher, I came in first.

00:58:55.733 --> 00:58:56.566
That fast?

00:58:56.566 --> 00:58:57.866
[After all, she learned from Jack]

00:58:58.400 --> 00:58:59.033
Now I look so slow.

00:59:00.300 --> 00:59:01.966
It's fine, don't be nervous.

00:59:01.966 --> 00:59:03.700
Ours can make yours stand out.

00:59:07.433 --> 00:59:08.500
[Lily finished]
I'm done too.

00:59:08.533 --> 00:59:09.933
I'm a bit slow here.

00:59:10.733 --> 00:59:11.933
It's fine.

00:59:16.766 --> 00:59:18.700
Club president, yours is so good.

00:59:18.733 --> 00:59:19.400
Done.

00:59:19.400 --> 00:59:21.866
[Keeps praising]
Is this the work of a modern artist?

00:59:22.233 --> 00:59:23.733
That's so articulate.

00:59:27.233 --> 00:59:28.266
[Voice arrives before sight]

00:59:28.300 --> 00:59:29.000
Did you see it?

00:59:29.000 --> 00:59:30.433
[I really can't tell]
What is that?

00:59:30.433 --> 00:59:31.233
That one.

00:59:31.733 --> 00:59:33.033
[Give some emotional support]

00:59:33.333 --> 00:59:35.833
Alright, that's it.

00:59:35.833 --> 00:59:36.866
Around this part.

00:59:38.533 --> 00:59:39.266
It's...

00:59:43.000 --> 00:59:43.466
What is it?

00:59:43.733 --> 00:59:44.366
[Is it really that hard?]
Stop it.

00:59:44.633 --> 00:59:45.933
[A little abstract]

00:59:46.366 --> 00:59:48.500
It's a goat.

00:59:48.533 --> 00:59:48.766
Right.

00:59:48.766 --> 00:59:50.166
And it's...

00:59:50.166 --> 00:59:50.833
Grass.

00:59:52.766 --> 00:59:54.633
[Huh?]

00:59:54.933 --> 00:59:56.566
I could tell that was grass.

00:59:56.933 --> 00:59:58.866
But it really looks like a rabbit.

00:59:58.900 --> 01:00:01.033
It's fine. It's just a painting...

01:00:02.700 --> 01:00:03.600
[Different takes]
Everyone does, yeah.

01:00:03.600 --> 01:00:06.066
Isn't there something
about Hamlet, right?

01:00:06.100 --> 01:00:07.133
Yeah.

01:00:08.500 --> 01:00:09.833
I drew two.

01:00:09.833 --> 01:00:10.866
The first is simple.

01:00:12.933 --> 01:00:13.566
Panda.

01:00:13.566 --> 01:00:14.166
[Instant answer]

01:00:15.000 --> 01:00:16.133
Right, that was easy.

01:00:17.166 --> 01:00:18.366
And the second one? This one.

01:00:18.800 --> 01:00:19.600
It's kind of abstract.

01:00:21.300 --> 01:00:22.033
The Great Wall?

01:00:23.600 --> 01:00:24.200
Dragon?

01:00:25.200 --> 01:00:25.833
Yes.

01:00:25.833 --> 01:00:26.866
How did you guess so accurately?

01:00:30.133 --> 01:00:31.066
[I'm confused]
Why?

01:00:31.100 --> 01:00:32.933
Don't you think this is imposing?

01:00:32.933 --> 01:00:33.600
[Imposing]

01:00:35.233 --> 01:00:36.466
[Self-doubt]
Is it imposing?

01:00:36.833 --> 01:00:37.833
[Still quite similar]
But it also looks like a dragon.

01:00:38.600 --> 01:00:38.933
This...

01:00:38.966 --> 01:00:40.700
Yeah, exactly.

01:00:40.733 --> 01:00:41.600
Very similar.

01:00:42.133 --> 01:00:42.733
Professional.

01:00:43.500 --> 01:00:44.333
Very professional.

01:00:46.600 --> 01:00:48.400
Two of them.

01:00:48.400 --> 01:00:49.333
This one is a pig.

01:00:49.366 --> 01:00:50.366
[Pig]

01:00:50.366 --> 01:00:51.700
The one behind is a little mouse.

01:00:51.733 --> 01:00:52.833
A puppy.

01:00:52.833 --> 01:00:53.866
Yeah.

01:00:53.900 --> 01:00:56.366
Do you know the exact breed?

01:00:58.200 --> 01:00:59.333
[Dachshund?]

01:00:59.366 --> 01:01:00.100
No.

01:01:02.566 --> 01:01:03.633
[Poodle?]

01:01:03.633 --> 01:01:04.700
No.

01:01:06.800 --> 01:01:07.700
One that can fly.

01:01:09.900 --> 01:01:11.033
[No clue]

01:01:11.500 --> 01:01:12.166
[Beagle]

01:01:13.300 --> 01:01:15.366
Beagles bark with a "wer wer" sound.

01:01:18.033 --> 01:01:18.933
Do you have one?

01:01:19.700 --> 01:01:22.966
I probably wouldn't get a beagle.

01:01:22.966 --> 01:01:23.300
Why?

01:01:24.200 --> 01:01:25.300
Because it goes "wer wer".

01:01:25.333 --> 01:01:26.166
"Wer wer"?

01:01:26.166 --> 01:01:27.066
It goes "wer wer".

01:01:28.800 --> 01:01:30.100
I drew this.

01:01:30.733 --> 01:01:32.166
This is the first version.

01:01:32.166 --> 01:01:33.100
And this is the second version.

01:01:36.900 --> 01:01:37.600
A flamingo.

01:01:37.600 --> 01:01:38.300
Yeah.

01:01:38.333 --> 01:01:39.133
This looks so good.

01:01:41.733 --> 01:01:43.433
Okay, last student.

01:01:46.900 --> 01:01:47.766
It feels very story-driven.

01:01:47.766 --> 01:01:49.233
Right, this is winter.

01:01:49.566 --> 01:01:50.966
So it needs a scarf.

01:01:50.966 --> 01:01:52.066
Little pig in winter.

01:01:52.533 --> 01:01:53.466
Winter pig.

01:01:54.900 --> 01:01:55.966
Snow pig.

01:01:55.966 --> 01:01:57.300
Same as what you drew.

01:01:58.500 --> 01:01:59.500
Great minds think alike.

01:01:59.500 --> 01:02:00.200
Yeah.

01:02:04.166 --> 01:02:07.166
Welcome to the Badminton Club.

01:02:07.166 --> 01:02:08.600
Let's see what we've got.

01:02:10.733 --> 01:02:12.133
Why is there a deck of poker cards here?

01:02:14.433 --> 01:02:16.566
We can sit around and play cards.

01:02:17.933 --> 01:02:20.466
Next, let's play two games.

01:02:20.500 --> 01:02:21.500
Okay.

01:02:21.500 --> 01:02:22.600
The first game is

01:02:22.600 --> 01:02:25.533
[Lesson 1: Agility Training]
to use chopsticks to catch flying poker cards.

01:02:25.966 --> 01:02:27.000
[Chopsticks, badminton, poker cards]

01:02:27.000 --> 01:02:30.000
The rule is,
one throws, the other catches.

01:02:30.000 --> 01:02:31.300
[Look]
Then see how many poker cards are caught

01:02:31.333 --> 01:02:33.233
[Excited]
in one minute.

01:02:33.233 --> 01:02:33.866
Okay.

01:02:33.900 --> 01:02:35.100
Perfect, you can split into two teams.

01:02:35.200 --> 01:02:36.333
[Nora and Jason Team.
Eon and Zhaoyu Team]

01:02:36.433 --> 01:02:38.666
The club president should do one too.

01:02:38.700 --> 01:02:39.600
[I'll go first and show you]
Come on, help me throw them.

01:02:39.600 --> 01:02:40.133
I'll give it a try.

01:02:40.433 --> 01:02:41.966
I'll throw one at a time.

01:02:42.000 --> 01:02:43.400
Throw upwards.

01:02:43.400 --> 01:02:44.066
No, get closer.

01:02:44.700 --> 01:02:45.533
Wait a sec.

01:02:45.533 --> 01:02:46.433
[Prop upgrade in progress]
Are you ready?

01:02:46.433 --> 01:02:47.233
Nope.

01:02:47.233 --> 01:02:47.766
Throw it higher.

01:02:47.800 --> 01:02:48.100
Throw it.

01:02:48.133 --> 01:02:48.766
Come on.

01:02:53.000 --> 01:02:54.500
[I only need one quick move]

01:02:58.833 --> 01:02:59.700
[Sneaky poker cards]

01:03:03.400 --> 01:03:04.200
It's fine. Come on.

01:03:04.333 --> 01:03:05.633
[Reloading]

01:03:06.433 --> 01:03:07.900
It's fine. You've got 54 cards.

01:03:07.933 --> 01:03:08.600
[Miss +1].

01:03:08.833 --> 01:03:09.433
[Miss +2]

01:03:09.766 --> 01:03:10.400
[Miss +3]

01:03:10.600 --> 01:03:11.233
[Miss +4]

01:03:11.433 --> 01:03:12.266
[Miss +5]

01:03:12.966 --> 01:03:13.833
[Hit rate: 0]

01:03:17.733 --> 01:03:18.966
Okay, done.

01:03:18.966 --> 01:03:20.600
That's it. Got it?

01:03:20.600 --> 01:03:24.100
[University of Cambridge
doesn't train athletes]

01:03:24.300 --> 01:03:24.833
Wait, wait a sec.

01:03:24.833 --> 01:03:26.533
[Physics hack activated]
Try one.

01:03:26.566 --> 01:03:27.633
Clamp it, then set one here.

01:03:31.100 --> 01:03:32.100
Still can't hold it.

01:03:33.233 --> 01:03:34.266
Hold on, these chopsticks might...

01:03:34.300 --> 01:03:35.433
Grab it, come on.

01:03:35.433 --> 01:03:36.366
[Doctor Waterloo]
No, catch it.

01:03:36.400 --> 01:03:37.300
The chopsticks don't seem to catch.

01:03:38.433 --> 01:03:39.966
[Try the other side]

01:03:40.733 --> 01:03:42.166
Club president, not even this works?

01:03:42.166 --> 01:03:42.666
Club president.

01:03:43.966 --> 01:03:46.000
Club president, how do we learn now?

01:03:48.033 --> 01:03:49.533
[Timely save]

01:03:49.633 --> 01:03:50.233
How about this?

01:03:50.233 --> 01:03:51.266
We just need to touch it.

01:03:51.300 --> 01:03:52.366
As long as we touch it.

01:03:52.366 --> 01:03:53.033
[Rule change]

01:03:53.033 --> 01:03:54.566
[(Final interpretation rights
belong to the doctor)]

01:03:55.300 --> 01:03:56.400
Three, two, one.

01:04:00.133 --> 01:04:01.533
[Kind of hard]
Can't even hit it.

01:04:03.500 --> 01:04:04.133
Sorry.

01:04:05.733 --> 01:04:06.600
[Getting irritated]

01:04:06.633 --> 01:04:07.966
[Not quite as good as me]

01:04:08.100 --> 01:04:08.833
[A little closer]

01:04:10.233 --> 01:04:11.100
[Dodge]

01:04:11.500 --> 01:04:12.933
[Not quite as good as me]
You dodged them all.

01:04:12.933 --> 01:04:14.266
Still can't land a hit.

01:04:14.300 --> 01:04:15.200
Fruit Ninja.

01:04:15.766 --> 01:04:17.833
[Perfect dodge]

01:04:17.900 --> 01:04:19.433
[All that for nothing. Game Over]

01:04:19.800 --> 01:04:20.833
[Teamwork]

01:04:22.166 --> 01:04:22.700
[Hit]

01:04:23.233 --> 01:04:23.966
[Finally got 1 point]

01:04:26.500 --> 01:04:27.233
Got it.

01:04:27.233 --> 01:04:29.566
[Nora and Jason Team: 2 points]

01:04:29.600 --> 01:04:30.266
Count it.

01:04:30.300 --> 01:04:31.766
[Nora and Jason Team: 3 points]

01:04:31.766 --> 01:04:33.366
[Nora and Jason Team: 4 points]

01:04:33.366 --> 01:04:33.900
Okay, that one hit.

01:04:33.933 --> 01:04:34.366
That hit.

01:04:34.366 --> 01:04:35.400
[Nora and Jason Team: 5 points]

01:04:35.400 --> 01:04:36.300
[Nora and Jason Team: 6 points]
Nice, got it.

01:04:36.366 --> 01:04:37.500
[We're getting more in sync]

01:04:46.600 --> 01:04:47.200
That reaction speed.

01:04:47.200 --> 01:04:47.866
Okay, that's it.

01:04:49.400 --> 01:04:52.300
[Nora and Jason Team: 12 points]

01:04:52.966 --> 01:04:53.666
Come on.

01:04:53.700 --> 01:04:54.400
Go.

01:04:54.400 --> 01:04:55.133
[Look]

01:04:55.166 --> 01:04:55.800
Magic.

01:04:59.400 --> 01:04:59.733
One.

01:04:59.766 --> 01:05:00.300
[Eon and Zhaoyu Team: 1 point]

01:05:00.633 --> 01:05:02.333
I'll just toss it at you.

01:05:02.366 --> 01:05:03.833
Just toss it at you.

01:05:05.000 --> 01:05:06.466
[Five minutes earlier]
What if I miss?

01:05:06.500 --> 01:05:07.000
It's okay.

01:05:07.600 --> 01:05:09.133
[I'll just toss it at you]

01:05:09.166 --> 01:05:11.400
[Eon and Zhaoyu Team: 2 points]

01:05:11.400 --> 01:05:12.100
Three.

01:05:12.100 --> 01:05:13.000
[Eon and Zhaoyu Team: 3 points]

01:05:13.000 --> 01:05:14.800
[Eon and Zhaoyu Team: 4 points]

01:05:14.833 --> 01:05:16.433
[Eon and Zhaoyu Team: 5 points]

01:05:16.433 --> 01:05:17.100
[Eon and Zhaoyu Team: 6 points]

01:05:18.266 --> 01:05:19.300
Seven.

01:05:19.333 --> 01:05:20.500
[Eon and Zhaoyu Team: 7 points]

01:05:20.533 --> 01:05:23.466
[Eon and Zhaoyu Team: 8 points]

01:05:23.500 --> 01:05:24.300
[Eon and Zhaoyu Team: 9 points]
Got it.

01:05:25.800 --> 01:05:26.433
13.

01:05:27.100 --> 01:05:27.800
14.

01:05:28.300 --> 01:05:29.600
[Slow on the uptake]
Why'd you toss it right to her?

01:05:30.033 --> 01:05:31.333
[You don't get our rhythm]
You threw it straight to her.

01:05:31.900 --> 01:05:32.700
15.

01:05:33.000 --> 01:05:33.966
16.

01:05:34.000 --> 01:05:35.900
[Eon and Zhaoyu Team: 16 points]

01:05:35.933 --> 01:05:37.833
[Eon and Zhaoyu Team: 17 points]

01:05:37.833 --> 01:05:39.666
[Eon and Zhaoyu Team: 18 points]

01:05:39.700 --> 01:05:40.533
[Eon and Zhaoyu Team: 19 points]

01:05:40.900 --> 01:05:41.666
19.

01:05:42.000 --> 01:05:42.733
[Eon and Zhaoyu Team: 19 points]
So good.

01:05:43.700 --> 01:05:45.366
Zhaoyu Zhang reacts faster than I?

01:05:45.366 --> 01:05:46.000
[Useless man]

01:05:46.400 --> 01:05:48.933
I think it's because of Eon.

01:05:48.966 --> 01:05:50.400
[Praise]
He throws accurately.

01:05:50.400 --> 01:05:51.400
I think it's because of Eon.

01:05:51.400 --> 01:05:52.600
He throws accurately.

01:06:03.233 --> 01:06:04.500
And now,

01:06:04.533 --> 01:06:06.600
the next game is ball juggling.

01:06:06.600 --> 01:06:07.933
[Lesson 2: Teamwork]
You'll pair up.

01:06:07.966 --> 01:06:09.166
Tie your hands together.

01:06:09.166 --> 01:06:10.233
Within one minute,

01:06:10.233 --> 01:06:11.766
[Serious]
whoever gets more wins.

01:06:11.800 --> 01:06:12.833
[Listening]

01:06:12.933 --> 01:06:14.166
And your hands stay tied together.

01:06:14.166 --> 01:06:14.966
Come on, tie them up.

01:06:18.433 --> 01:06:18.966
And then?

01:06:19.000 --> 01:06:20.600
Then start juggling.

01:06:20.600 --> 01:06:22.000
What's my purpose here?

01:06:22.000 --> 01:06:23.600
You're here to make it harder for him.

01:06:27.766 --> 01:06:28.466
Feeling the pressure?

01:06:28.500 --> 01:06:29.533
[So stressed]
Absolutely.

01:06:29.533 --> 01:06:31.633
My goal is to juggle two.

01:06:31.633 --> 01:06:32.833
Two?

01:06:32.833 --> 01:06:33.433
Ready?

01:06:33.433 --> 01:06:34.633
Maybe.

01:06:34.633 --> 01:06:36.133
Three, two, one, go.

01:06:40.633 --> 01:06:42.300
[Inseparable]

01:06:44.933 --> 01:06:46.166
[Close behind]

01:06:46.166 --> 01:06:48.166
12, 13.

01:06:48.166 --> 01:06:50.066
Juggling isn't...

01:06:50.100 --> 01:06:51.000
[Immersive juggling]

01:06:52.433 --> 01:06:53.666
[The crowd goes wild]

01:06:53.766 --> 01:06:54.666
[Wow]

01:06:55.800 --> 01:06:56.733
So cool.

01:06:56.766 --> 01:06:57.400
So cool!

01:06:57.400 --> 01:06:58.500
[So cool]

01:07:07.600 --> 01:07:08.866
[Timing seriously]
10 seconds left. Come on.

01:07:11.900 --> 01:07:13.166
He's so good at this.

01:07:15.700 --> 01:07:16.166
Come on.

01:07:16.633 --> 01:07:17.900
[Time's up]

01:07:17.933 --> 01:07:18.866
Did you count?

01:07:18.900 --> 01:07:19.700
I lost count, too.

01:07:19.700 --> 01:07:21.700
I was just watching you play.

01:07:22.766 --> 01:07:23.400
No need to count now.

01:07:23.400 --> 01:07:25.300
[It's all about joining in]
Already no suspense at all.

01:07:25.333 --> 01:07:25.966
Come on.

01:07:25.966 --> 01:07:28.166
How about you hit three?

01:07:28.166 --> 01:07:28.966
Sure.

01:07:28.966 --> 01:07:29.700
Okay.

01:07:29.733 --> 01:07:30.466
Come on.

01:07:30.500 --> 01:07:31.533
We've got one minute.

01:07:32.366 --> 01:07:33.033
Ready?

01:07:34.133 --> 01:07:34.533
Be careful.

01:07:34.533 --> 01:07:35.566
[Friendly reminder]
It's a bit wet here.

01:07:35.566 --> 01:07:37.033
Then let's move over here.

01:07:37.033 --> 01:07:37.733
Come on.

01:07:37.766 --> 01:07:38.400
Go ahead.

01:07:39.900 --> 01:07:41.100
Three, two, one, go.

01:07:43.033 --> 01:07:43.833
[A rough start]

01:07:43.900 --> 01:07:44.766
[Not funny now]

01:07:44.766 --> 01:07:45.700
[Cheering]
You got this. I'll get it.

01:07:45.733 --> 01:07:46.666
Then hit it straight over.

01:07:46.700 --> 01:07:47.766
Come on.

01:07:47.766 --> 01:07:48.700
No, don't hit my hand.

01:07:51.766 --> 01:07:53.200
[Using both hands and feet]

01:07:53.566 --> 01:07:54.700
Three. Come on.

01:07:54.733 --> 01:07:55.633
[Quickly picking up on it]

01:07:55.633 --> 01:07:56.266
Take it slow.

01:07:58.800 --> 01:08:00.233
[Misses again]

01:08:00.400 --> 01:08:01.066
It's okay.

01:08:01.100 --> 01:08:01.833
[Encouragement +1]

01:08:04.700 --> 01:08:06.333
[Wow]

01:08:06.333 --> 01:08:07.366
[Combo x3]
Three. Nice.

01:08:07.366 --> 01:08:08.066
That's really good.

01:08:11.133 --> 01:08:12.666
[Amazing save]

01:08:13.200 --> 01:08:14.033
That counts too.

01:08:14.033 --> 01:08:15.133
It counts.

01:08:15.166 --> 01:08:15.666
Keep it up.

01:08:16.000 --> 01:08:16.866
[Time's up]

01:08:17.233 --> 01:08:19.100
[Nora and Jason Team: 7 points]
Nice.

01:08:19.133 --> 01:08:19.766
Great job.

01:08:19.766 --> 01:08:20.200
Thanks.

01:08:20.200 --> 01:08:21.933
Now it's the badminton match.

01:08:22.233 --> 01:08:23.466
[Warm-up over. Match starts now]

01:08:23.533 --> 01:08:24.400
[Ready and focused]

01:08:24.433 --> 01:08:25.366
[Waiting for the move]

01:08:25.400 --> 01:08:26.666
The ultimate showdown.

01:08:27.300 --> 01:08:27.900
[Quick dodge]

01:08:36.533 --> 01:08:37.866
[Leans in for the save]

01:08:38.633 --> 01:08:39.566
[Wow]

01:08:41.333 --> 01:08:42.966
Your athletic skills are maxed out.

01:08:44.300 --> 01:08:45.700
[Diving save]

01:08:51.033 --> 01:08:51.933
Okay, it's 1:0 now.

01:08:53.366 --> 01:08:55.200
[Loses a point]

01:09:02.566 --> 01:09:03.066
[Concerned]

01:09:03.100 --> 01:09:03.566
You okay?

01:09:03.566 --> 01:09:04.466
I'm fine. Really.

01:09:05.566 --> 01:09:07.900
[Powering up...]

01:09:21.633 --> 01:09:22.133
You okay?

01:09:22.166 --> 01:09:22.600
I'm fine.

01:09:22.600 --> 01:09:23.666
It's 2:1 now.

01:09:23.833 --> 01:09:24.866
[Wins a point]

01:09:29.633 --> 01:09:31.033
Eon, you're amazing.

01:09:40.500 --> 01:09:40.900
Nice.

01:09:40.900 --> 01:09:42.033
It's tied at 2:2 now.

01:09:42.033 --> 01:09:43.033
Now there's just one last.

01:09:43.033 --> 01:09:43.966
Last point, right?

01:09:44.000 --> 01:09:44.866
Match point.

01:09:44.900 --> 01:09:46.033
Who will take the win?

01:09:46.300 --> 01:09:48.133
[The deciding point]

01:09:58.633 --> 01:09:59.666
Alright, then.

01:09:59.700 --> 01:10:00.333
They won.

01:10:00.833 --> 01:10:01.866
[Signature celebration reappears]
Alright, then.

01:10:01.900 --> 01:10:02.233
Beautiful.

01:10:02.233 --> 01:10:02.833
They won.

01:10:02.833 --> 01:10:03.466
Congrats, you two.

01:10:03.500 --> 01:10:04.400
Congrats.

01:10:06.966 --> 01:10:07.800
Badminton king.

01:10:08.400 --> 01:10:09.033
Awesome.

01:10:11.233 --> 01:10:12.333
We've still got basketball.

01:10:12.366 --> 01:10:13.300
Come on, free throws.

01:10:16.600 --> 01:10:17.666
Show us

01:10:17.700 --> 01:10:19.133
your best shot.

01:10:20.300 --> 01:10:21.800
[Excited]

01:10:22.833 --> 01:10:24.166
Give us a quick demo.

01:10:30.533 --> 01:10:31.800
[Swish]

01:10:35.633 --> 01:10:36.500
That's amazing.

01:10:40.133 --> 01:10:42.000
How about a half-court three?

01:10:42.000 --> 01:10:42.533
You want me to?

01:10:46.833 --> 01:10:47.300
Let's see.

01:10:47.333 --> 01:10:48.000
See how far I can go.

01:10:49.366 --> 01:10:50.033
[Walks off-screen]

01:10:50.033 --> 01:10:50.533
From that far?

01:10:50.566 --> 01:10:51.233
That far away?

01:10:51.400 --> 01:10:52.933
[Watching closely]

01:11:21.033 --> 01:11:22.133
That's insane.

01:11:30.400 --> 01:11:31.266
Keep going.

01:11:35.433 --> 01:11:36.666
Slam Dunk Master.

01:11:36.700 --> 01:11:38.500
Just like Eon taught you.

01:11:45.200 --> 01:11:46.066
Club president.

01:11:46.100 --> 01:11:47.000
Club president, slow down.

01:11:47.700 --> 01:11:48.833
I'll stop here.

01:11:48.833 --> 01:11:49.766
Too abstract?

01:11:49.800 --> 01:11:50.733
I guessed it.

01:11:50.766 --> 01:11:51.566
Was it a fish?

01:11:52.600 --> 01:11:53.233
Pretty close.

01:11:57.533 --> 01:11:58.833
Today's club is over.

01:11:58.833 --> 01:11:59.533
I had a great time.

01:11:59.566 --> 01:11:59.766
So fun.

01:11:59.766 --> 01:12:01.200
Yes.

01:12:07.100 --> 01:12:09.000
Today's drawings were so fun.

01:12:09.000 --> 01:12:10.933
This is the whale I drew today.

01:12:10.966 --> 01:12:12.500
And the sun, and a whale shark.

01:12:12.533 --> 01:12:14.033
And someone is skiing too.

01:12:14.033 --> 01:12:15.266
Everyone felt so creative.

01:12:15.300 --> 01:12:15.833
Yeah.

01:12:15.833 --> 01:12:17.966
Everyone painted different seasons.

01:12:18.000 --> 01:12:19.700
With a robot dog and a house.

01:12:19.733 --> 01:12:21.066
It was really fun.

01:12:21.100 --> 01:12:22.333
I want to take a photo.

01:12:23.200 --> 01:12:25.400
Post a moment on Soul.

01:12:25.400 --> 01:12:27.433
Then share everyone's artwork.

01:12:27.433 --> 01:12:28.433
You can find more painting buddies

01:12:28.433 --> 01:12:29.766
on Soul.

01:12:29.800 --> 01:12:30.866
We can also meet

01:12:30.900 --> 01:12:31.833
more creative friends.

01:12:31.833 --> 01:12:32.500
Yeah.

01:12:32.700 --> 01:12:33.833
Post it.

01:12:44.966 --> 01:12:47.166
Yeah, it's posted.

01:12:47.166 --> 01:12:48.033
[Yuna. Painting Masters #Twinkle Love in Winter Painter]
I'll go check later

01:12:48.033 --> 01:12:48.766
and leave a like.

01:12:48.800 --> 01:12:49.466
Okay.

01:12:50.900 --> 01:12:53.500
Our Study Activity

01:12:53.500 --> 01:12:54.966
is pretty much wrapping up.

01:12:55.366 --> 01:12:57.866
Next up, we have a really amazing

01:12:57.900 --> 01:13:00.933
team dinner by the snowy mountain.

01:13:02.000 --> 01:13:03.200
Alright, let's get going.

01:13:03.200 --> 01:13:03.900
Okay.

01:13:03.933 --> 01:13:04.666
Thank you, teacher.

01:13:07.766 --> 01:13:10.266
The snowy mountain...

01:13:16.600 --> 01:13:17.766
So beautiful.

01:13:18.533 --> 01:13:20.066
Looks so warm.

01:13:20.766 --> 01:13:21.766
A bonfire.

01:13:21.766 --> 01:13:22.600
So pretty.

01:13:23.333 --> 01:13:24.600
It's a real fire.

01:13:28.700 --> 01:13:29.733
Come on, let's go eat inside.

01:13:29.733 --> 01:13:30.600
[Mountain Cafe Fusion Cuisine]

01:13:30.600 --> 01:13:31.233
Let's go.

01:13:32.633 --> 01:13:33.533
[Yeah!]

01:13:33.733 --> 01:13:34.600
[Whoa]

01:13:36.100 --> 01:13:37.533
How should we sit?

01:13:37.533 --> 01:13:39.133
[How should we sit?]

01:13:39.133 --> 01:13:40.000
What's the seating plan?

01:13:41.300 --> 01:13:42.200
How are we sitting?

01:13:42.200 --> 01:13:43.300
Do we leave a seat between us?

01:13:43.333 --> 01:13:44.266
Or what?

01:13:44.300 --> 01:13:47.533
[Stay close]
This...

01:13:47.533 --> 01:13:48.166
Just sit wherever.

01:13:50.766 --> 01:13:52.466
[Watching]

01:13:53.133 --> 01:13:54.333
Then I'll sit here.

01:13:56.400 --> 01:13:57.633
My arms are long. I can reach.

01:13:57.633 --> 01:13:58.700
[Sits next to Nora]

01:14:06.733 --> 01:14:07.400
Then I'll sit here.

01:14:07.400 --> 01:14:08.266
Anywhere is fine.

01:14:08.300 --> 01:14:09.033
[Selected]

01:14:11.333 --> 01:14:11.966
I'll take this seat.

01:14:11.966 --> 01:14:12.833
[Selected]

01:14:13.000 --> 01:14:15.066
[Auto navigation]

01:14:15.166 --> 01:14:17.633
[Reserved]

01:14:29.733 --> 01:14:31.933
[I still couldn't do it tonight]

01:14:31.933 --> 01:14:33.833
[Feels like I missed a big day]

01:14:33.833 --> 01:14:34.700
[Yuna sits down]

01:14:40.833 --> 01:14:42.566
[Hao Chen sits by Yuna too]

01:14:44.133 --> 01:14:45.666
You know, it's cooling down now.

01:14:45.700 --> 01:14:48.600
[Suddenly talking]
Today is Ant Moving Day.

01:14:50.233 --> 01:14:51.866
Ant Moving Day?

01:14:51.900 --> 01:14:52.766
[Moving day?]
What does that mean?

01:14:53.633 --> 01:14:55.833
Because when I was
walking outside today,

01:14:55.833 --> 01:14:57.500
I passed by an ant.

01:14:59.000 --> 01:15:01.033
It got lost, probably.

01:15:01.033 --> 01:15:02.066
[Got lost]
And then,

01:15:02.100 --> 01:15:04.233
it might be asking another ant.

01:15:04.233 --> 01:15:05.933
"Hey, classmate,

01:15:05.966 --> 01:15:06.966
I'm lost."

01:15:07.933 --> 01:15:11.800
[How do you get back home?]

01:15:11.800 --> 01:15:13.466
Do you know what that ant said?

01:15:20.900 --> 01:15:23.433
How do you remember me?

01:15:24.733 --> 01:15:25.400
I'll sleep first.

01:15:25.500 --> 01:15:27.200
[How do you remember me?]

01:15:27.200 --> 01:15:28.600
[How do you get back home?]

01:15:28.733 --> 01:15:29.666
[With a smile or in silence]
Was that it?

01:15:29.700 --> 01:15:30.366
Yeah.

01:15:33.033 --> 01:15:33.766
Hurry.

01:15:37.166 --> 01:15:38.266
I really love this.

01:15:38.300 --> 01:15:39.733
I really love this joke.

01:15:43.200 --> 01:15:44.000
So cheesy.

01:15:44.000 --> 01:15:47.666
[Everyone's sense of humor differs]

01:15:47.933 --> 01:15:49.366
It was cheesy already.

01:15:51.566 --> 01:15:52.766
The temperature dropped.

01:15:53.500 --> 01:15:54.433
I'm done talking.

01:15:54.433 --> 01:15:55.066
It can't get any cheesier.

01:15:57.600 --> 01:15:58.533
So cute.

01:15:59.000 --> 01:16:00.600
So what's your talent act?

01:16:00.600 --> 01:16:01.433
[Curious]
Right.

01:16:02.400 --> 01:16:04.433
I actually haven't shown

01:16:04.433 --> 01:16:06.033
my guitar yet.

01:16:08.566 --> 01:16:10.000
Let me do that.

01:16:10.000 --> 01:16:11.066
Go ahead.

01:16:18.733 --> 01:16:19.533
Is this a guitar?

01:16:21.300 --> 01:16:23.000
That's so cool.

01:16:23.500 --> 01:16:24.500
Hold on, let me warm up.

01:16:24.700 --> 01:16:27.366
[Beep]

01:16:40.433 --> 01:16:43.333
♪The night breeze stirs the bamboo♪

01:16:43.633 --> 01:16:46.600
♪Moonlight stretches our shadows♪

01:16:46.833 --> 01:16:49.933
♪Fireflies flicker and glow♪

01:16:50.366 --> 01:16:52.900
♪Like coins dancing on the hills♪

01:16:53.100 --> 01:16:56.033
♪The Milky Way shines above♪

01:16:56.300 --> 01:16:59.166
♪Wind chimes sing here below♪

01:16:59.433 --> 01:17:02.300
♪Vega shines in the distance♪

01:17:03.000 --> 01:17:05.700
♪An ancient romantic tale♪

01:17:06.066 --> 01:17:08.866
♪Cherry blossoms in lovers' embrace♪

01:17:09.200 --> 01:17:11.966
♪I hear my heartbeat racing♪

01:17:12.333 --> 01:17:15.233
♪Quietly, I'm missing you♪

01:17:15.500 --> 01:17:20.733
♪That's our sign of love♪

01:17:21.800 --> 01:17:22.900
Thanks.

01:17:24.200 --> 01:17:25.733
Total flop.

01:17:25.766 --> 01:17:26.566
Sounds great.

01:17:26.566 --> 01:17:27.300
Really good.

01:17:27.333 --> 01:17:28.033
It's great.

01:17:28.033 --> 01:17:29.733
Thanks.

01:17:29.766 --> 01:17:32.200
So you've all performed?

01:17:32.200 --> 01:17:33.266
Yes.

01:17:33.300 --> 01:17:34.633
Yes!

01:17:34.633 --> 01:17:36.666
What kinds of talents?

01:17:36.700 --> 01:17:37.500
Fire-breathing.

01:17:39.133 --> 01:17:39.933
Fire-breathing?

01:17:39.933 --> 01:17:40.733
Hoops jumping.

01:17:40.733 --> 01:17:42.433
And backflips.

01:17:42.433 --> 01:17:44.466
Yes, the fire hoop kind.

01:17:45.633 --> 01:17:46.966
Someone's talent back then...

01:17:47.000 --> 01:17:47.866
Wasn't it like that?

01:17:47.900 --> 01:17:48.766
I forgot who it was.

01:17:48.766 --> 01:17:50.833
[Pretending not to know]
But I want to learn it.

01:17:52.966 --> 01:17:54.633
[Watching you silently]

01:17:55.566 --> 01:17:57.233
[You're doing this on purpose]

01:17:58.500 --> 01:17:59.333
Sorry.

01:17:59.333 --> 01:17:59.933
I'm sorry.

01:17:59.933 --> 01:18:00.566
[Hmph]

01:18:01.600 --> 01:18:02.433
Can you perform it again?

01:18:02.433 --> 01:18:04.533
[Angry...]
I practiced so hard after going back.

01:18:04.566 --> 01:18:05.966
But I still couldn't do it.

01:18:05.966 --> 01:18:07.000
[Wronged]

01:18:07.400 --> 01:18:09.033
You even forgot who did it.

01:18:09.033 --> 01:18:11.066
And you want another show? No.

01:18:11.833 --> 01:18:12.566
Keep dreaming.

01:18:12.600 --> 01:18:13.800
[Joke fell flat]

01:18:14.333 --> 01:18:15.666
What's your special skill, girl?

01:18:18.933 --> 01:18:20.333
I can make something for you.

01:18:20.400 --> 01:18:22.066
[Wanting it]

01:18:22.100 --> 01:18:23.633
Something you really want.

01:18:26.400 --> 01:18:27.333
Three, two.

01:18:36.600 --> 01:18:38.300
I want one too.

01:18:38.333 --> 01:18:38.833
Come on.

01:18:39.766 --> 01:18:41.166
One, two, three.

01:18:41.733 --> 01:18:42.633
[Wow]

01:18:42.766 --> 01:18:43.966
This one's different.

01:18:44.200 --> 01:18:45.633
[I want one]

01:18:45.833 --> 01:18:47.433
One, two, three.

01:18:48.433 --> 01:18:50.233
[Wow]

01:18:51.133 --> 01:18:52.000
They're all different.

01:18:52.000 --> 01:18:53.066
Got it.

01:18:53.100 --> 01:18:54.566
Put it away safely.

01:18:54.933 --> 01:18:56.233
[Polite]

01:18:59.733 --> 01:19:00.533
What do you want to drink?

01:19:00.533 --> 01:19:01.400
What do you guys want to drink?

01:19:03.433 --> 01:19:04.366
[What do you want to drink?]

01:19:05.166 --> 01:19:06.233
I want orange juice.

01:19:11.200 --> 01:19:12.500
[Grabbing juice]

01:19:14.333 --> 01:19:15.266
Who wants orange juice?

01:19:15.300 --> 01:19:16.033
I want coffee.

01:19:16.033 --> 01:19:16.500
[Reaches out hard]

01:19:16.766 --> 01:19:17.500
[Handing it to Yuna]
Do you want coffee?

01:19:19.500 --> 01:19:20.533
[Pulling back]

01:19:20.533 --> 01:19:23.066
[Pauses]
I thought Eon wanted the orange juice.

01:19:23.100 --> 01:19:24.300
[Juice intended for Yuna]
Then I'll wait.

01:19:25.233 --> 01:19:26.733
[Putting juice down]

01:19:34.933 --> 01:19:36.866
[Hungry]
Let's eat.

01:19:36.900 --> 01:19:38.433
Feels like afternoon now.

01:19:38.433 --> 01:19:39.733
Because I'm having afternoon tea.

01:19:46.766 --> 01:19:47.566
So elegant.

01:19:48.533 --> 01:19:49.266
Exactly.

01:19:49.300 --> 01:19:50.233
Right.

01:19:50.233 --> 01:19:51.066
So right.

01:19:51.100 --> 01:19:52.833
Drinking a bowl of spicy pepper soup
early in the morning.

01:19:55.433 --> 01:19:56.866
[Wordplay mode on]
So right, so hot.

01:19:56.900 --> 01:19:58.200
Come to Henan this weekend.

01:19:58.200 --> 01:19:59.033
[Heartily]
Come on, let's cheer.

01:19:59.633 --> 01:20:00.166
Come on.

01:20:00.733 --> 01:20:01.200
Right.

01:20:01.200 --> 01:20:03.100
[Let's compete in Central Plains!]
Cheers.

01:20:03.133 --> 01:20:04.166
Let's do it.

01:20:04.166 --> 01:20:06.233
Welcome, new classmates.

01:20:06.233 --> 01:20:07.133
Thanks.

01:20:08.566 --> 01:20:10.566
Wishing us a joyful journey.

01:20:10.566 --> 01:20:10.900
A great trip.

01:20:10.933 --> 01:20:11.566
Definitely.

01:20:15.066 --> 01:20:16.233
Right, four against one.

01:20:16.233 --> 01:20:16.666
[Got it]

01:20:18.966 --> 01:20:19.866
Thanks.

01:20:29.366 --> 01:20:30.100
[Wow]

01:20:30.333 --> 01:20:31.400
[Wow...]

01:20:32.366 --> 01:20:34.266
[Confirming glances]

01:20:34.300 --> 01:20:34.966
It's...

01:20:34.966 --> 01:20:35.400
[Wow]

01:20:35.400 --> 01:20:36.233
What's that flavor?

01:20:36.233 --> 01:20:39.766
Like pork floss mixed with rice.

01:20:41.800 --> 01:20:43.066
It's kind of amazing.

01:20:43.100 --> 01:20:43.566
Is it good?

01:20:43.933 --> 01:20:45.433
Yeah, it's good.

01:20:45.433 --> 01:20:46.933
[In sync]
What do you want for hotpot?

01:20:46.966 --> 01:20:47.966
Hotpot.

01:20:49.900 --> 01:20:50.900
Put some in.

01:20:50.900 --> 01:20:51.533
[Okay]

01:20:51.533 --> 01:20:53.366
Just put anything, right?

01:20:53.366 --> 01:20:55.300
[Taking action immediately]

01:21:03.966 --> 01:21:07.033
[Can't hide smile]

01:21:07.533 --> 01:21:08.733
Want some, Yuna?

01:21:09.133 --> 01:21:09.833
Yeah, I do.

01:21:09.833 --> 01:21:10.633
Thanks.

01:21:10.633 --> 01:21:11.366
Thanks...

01:21:12.500 --> 01:21:13.166
Thanks.

01:21:13.533 --> 01:21:15.466
[Precision feeding]

01:21:15.500 --> 01:21:16.133
Thanks.

01:21:16.833 --> 01:21:17.933
That's enough.

01:21:17.966 --> 01:21:19.166
Thanks. Try some.

01:21:26.133 --> 01:21:26.933
Do you want some?

01:21:26.933 --> 01:21:27.633
[Still feeding]
I got it.

01:21:27.633 --> 01:21:28.233
Let me do it.

01:21:29.033 --> 01:21:30.666
I want baby cabbage.

01:21:31.766 --> 01:21:32.466
Thanks.

01:21:33.233 --> 01:21:33.633
Thanks...

01:21:33.633 --> 01:21:34.266
It's okay.

01:21:34.900 --> 01:21:35.566
Thanks.

01:21:37.800 --> 01:21:39.433
Maybe I'll do it?

01:21:40.633 --> 01:21:41.300
Or...

01:21:41.333 --> 01:21:41.733
Okay.

01:21:41.733 --> 01:21:42.400
I'll do it.

01:21:43.600 --> 01:21:44.266
Let me.

01:21:55.733 --> 01:21:58.400
[Graceful and poised]

01:21:59.133 --> 01:22:00.000
He's so graceful.

01:22:02.400 --> 01:22:07.733
[Elegant gentleman]

01:22:08.733 --> 01:22:09.666
How should I stand?

01:22:13.100 --> 01:22:14.800
It's okay. I'll help you.

01:22:14.800 --> 01:22:15.400
[Steps in to help]
Okay.

01:22:17.333 --> 01:22:18.533
Take a look.

01:22:18.533 --> 01:22:19.133
Okay.

01:22:19.133 --> 01:22:20.166
[In sync]

01:22:20.166 --> 01:22:20.833
Does this work?

01:22:20.833 --> 01:22:21.733
[Working together]

01:22:24.733 --> 01:22:25.566
Come on.

01:22:25.566 --> 01:22:26.200
Got it.

01:22:26.566 --> 01:22:27.033
Where should I put this?

01:22:27.833 --> 01:22:28.666
Thanks.

01:22:37.600 --> 01:22:39.233
Wow, that's a lot of stuff.

01:22:40.400 --> 01:22:42.700
Eat more while you're growing.
You're so thin.

01:22:42.733 --> 01:22:45.000
[I'm not... not really]

01:22:45.000 --> 01:22:46.733
Like a family reunion.

01:22:46.766 --> 01:22:48.100
[Relatives during Chinese New Year in Henan]
Come on. Eat more.

01:22:48.133 --> 01:22:48.666
Eat some more.

01:22:48.700 --> 01:22:50.600
Sure, works for me.

01:22:53.900 --> 01:22:55.100
Are you all from Henan?

01:22:55.100 --> 01:22:56.333
No, I'm from Shandong.

01:22:57.700 --> 01:22:58.933
Shandong has handsome guys.

01:22:58.933 --> 01:22:59.833
Shanghai has handsome guys, too.

01:22:59.833 --> 01:23:01.233
[Mutual flattery]

01:23:01.366 --> 01:23:01.966
What do you mean?

01:23:02.733 --> 01:23:03.600
Shanghai has pretty girls, too.

01:23:04.433 --> 01:23:04.733
Exactly.

01:23:06.533 --> 01:23:06.966
You two,

01:23:06.966 --> 01:23:08.400
can you describe each of us?

01:23:08.400 --> 01:23:08.900
Your first impression.

01:23:08.933 --> 01:23:09.533
Or a first impression.

01:23:09.766 --> 01:23:10.400
I want to know too.

01:23:10.400 --> 01:23:11.200
Isn't it?

01:23:11.200 --> 01:23:12.400
I'll start with the easiest.

01:23:12.700 --> 01:23:13.933
[Looking forward to it]

01:23:15.333 --> 01:23:15.800
Loves...

01:23:15.800 --> 01:23:16.800
studying German.

01:23:16.800 --> 01:23:17.900
Loves studying German.

01:23:18.966 --> 01:23:22.366
[Loves studying German]

01:23:22.933 --> 01:23:24.066
Elegant.

01:23:24.100 --> 01:23:24.700
Elegant...

01:23:24.700 --> 01:23:26.600
[Elegant]

01:23:27.166 --> 01:23:28.300
I just love studying German.

01:23:28.333 --> 01:23:29.600
And she's elegant?

01:23:29.600 --> 01:23:31.333
Loving German is elegant too.

01:23:31.366 --> 01:23:32.400
Okay, that works.

01:23:33.233 --> 01:23:34.866
Next.

01:23:34.900 --> 01:23:35.700
Dimples.

01:23:35.700 --> 01:23:37.200
[Dimples]

01:23:37.200 --> 01:23:38.733
You really notice details.

01:23:38.766 --> 01:23:39.400
Lively.

01:23:39.433 --> 01:23:40.966
[Lively]

01:23:41.533 --> 01:23:42.233
Good at playing along.

01:23:42.233 --> 01:23:44.233
[Good at playing along]

01:23:44.533 --> 01:23:45.333
And then...

01:23:46.333 --> 01:23:49.400
PhD.

01:23:49.833 --> 01:23:50.533
PhD?

01:23:51.233 --> 01:23:51.933
PhD!

01:23:52.600 --> 01:23:54.633
Alright, I'll be Dr. Bro then.

01:23:57.166 --> 01:23:57.900
Introverted.

01:23:59.533 --> 01:24:01.600
And you look like

01:24:01.600 --> 01:24:02.433
Chen Xuedong.

01:24:03.566 --> 01:24:04.600
[Let me take a look]

01:24:04.600 --> 01:24:05.933
That means celeb face.

01:24:05.966 --> 01:24:06.700
Right.

01:24:10.000 --> 01:24:11.633
You're...

01:24:11.633 --> 01:24:12.333
very literary.

01:24:13.166 --> 01:24:15.966
You really went off
in literature class today.

01:24:16.766 --> 01:24:18.800
And also,

01:24:18.800 --> 01:24:20.633
your features are super defined, right?

01:24:20.633 --> 01:24:21.533
[A sharply sculpted face]

01:24:21.566 --> 01:24:23.400
Well, what I said about Chen Xuedong.

01:24:23.400 --> 01:24:24.666
[Copying answers]

01:24:24.700 --> 01:24:25.600
And he is

01:24:25.600 --> 01:24:26.466
really good at basketball.

01:24:27.533 --> 01:24:28.533
And she is

01:24:28.533 --> 01:24:30.533
very outgoing, from my hometown.

01:24:30.533 --> 01:24:32.000
And she guessed

01:24:32.000 --> 01:24:33.066
my major exactly right.

01:24:35.000 --> 01:24:36.600
And she is

01:24:36.600 --> 01:24:37.300
really tall and slim.

01:24:39.300 --> 01:24:40.000
Tall and slim.

01:24:40.000 --> 01:24:40.300
Yeah.

01:24:40.333 --> 01:24:41.833
Why is there "tall" each time?

01:24:41.833 --> 01:24:42.333
Literal meaning.

01:24:42.366 --> 01:24:42.800
Literally.

01:24:43.033 --> 01:24:43.666
Okay.

01:24:43.700 --> 01:24:44.500
And she

01:24:45.766 --> 01:24:46.366
can play

01:24:46.366 --> 01:24:47.500
that instrument.

01:24:47.533 --> 01:24:48.766
And she sings really well.

01:24:51.166 --> 01:24:53.466
Shall we play a game?

01:24:53.500 --> 01:24:55.100
I just thought of one.

01:24:55.100 --> 01:24:56.533
Mirror imitation.

01:24:56.533 --> 01:24:59.066
Each person copies

01:24:59.100 --> 01:25:00.333
the previous person's action

01:25:00.333 --> 01:25:02.633
exactly.

01:25:04.566 --> 01:25:05.766
And the punishment...

01:25:05.833 --> 01:25:07.133
[Truth or Dare]

01:25:07.166 --> 01:25:07.666
Okay.

01:25:07.700 --> 01:25:08.133
Can we do that?

01:25:08.133 --> 01:25:08.866
Sure.

01:25:08.900 --> 01:25:10.100
Then I'll go first.

01:25:10.100 --> 01:25:10.833
Okay.

01:25:10.833 --> 01:25:12.266
[Round 1: Jack imitates]

01:25:13.300 --> 01:25:14.233
What is this?

01:25:14.233 --> 01:25:16.166
Put your thumb against your hand.

01:25:22.033 --> 01:25:22.966
I think I can do it.

01:25:23.000 --> 01:25:24.466
Like this? Is this right?

01:25:25.100 --> 01:25:26.033
I think I can too.

01:25:26.033 --> 01:25:27.366
Do I have some issue or what?

01:25:30.900 --> 01:25:32.033
Okay, bring on the penalty.

01:25:32.033 --> 01:25:33.166
Truth or Dare?

01:25:33.200 --> 01:25:33.900
Truth.

01:25:34.900 --> 01:25:37.000
[Jack takes the Truth challenge]
Describe your ideal type in three words.

01:25:37.733 --> 01:25:44.633
[Q: Describe your ideal type
in three words]

01:25:44.633 --> 01:25:47.100
[Sweet, unique, classy]

01:25:52.600 --> 01:25:54.500
My turn. It's a hand thing too.

01:25:54.533 --> 01:25:56.200
Like this, this part sticks out.

01:25:56.200 --> 01:25:57.200
[Round 2: Jack and Olivia imitate]

01:25:57.333 --> 01:25:58.200
It goes like this.

01:25:58.200 --> 01:25:59.466
It looks like a little table.

01:26:01.600 --> 01:26:03.333
[Failed again!]

01:26:03.366 --> 01:26:04.633
Everyone says this joint of mine

01:26:04.633 --> 01:26:05.333
can push sideways like this.

01:26:05.366 --> 01:26:06.266
[Trying hard]

01:26:06.300 --> 01:26:07.833
Is this the normal way?

01:26:07.833 --> 01:26:09.466
Or is my way the normal one?

01:26:10.600 --> 01:26:11.233
[Putting away tiny table]

01:26:12.200 --> 01:26:14.100
Well, that's it. You both failed.

01:26:14.133 --> 01:26:14.933
What?

01:26:14.933 --> 01:26:15.866
What do you mean?

01:26:15.900 --> 01:26:17.200
Truth or Dare, pick one.

01:26:18.500 --> 01:26:19.166
Dare.

01:26:19.566 --> 01:26:20.600
[Dare]

01:26:20.966 --> 01:26:22.500
Let me think.

01:26:23.233 --> 01:26:24.466
Go tap

01:26:24.500 --> 01:26:25.566
the one you noticed first

01:26:25.566 --> 01:26:26.400
upon entering.

01:26:26.400 --> 01:26:27.733
Your first impression when seeing us.

01:26:27.766 --> 01:26:29.233
[Dare: Tap the one you noticed first]
Should we all close our eyes?

01:26:29.233 --> 01:26:29.500
Yeah.

01:26:29.533 --> 01:26:30.266
Everyone, close your eyes.

01:26:30.300 --> 01:26:30.966
Okay.

01:26:33.933 --> 01:26:34.633
Me first.

01:26:34.633 --> 01:26:44.233
[Jack's Dare: Tap the one noticed first]

01:26:44.266 --> 01:26:46.033
I checked out your profile

01:26:46.066 --> 01:26:47.833
and wanted to invite you.

01:26:54.500 --> 01:26:54.966
At first sight?

01:26:55.366 --> 01:26:55.966
Yeah, just first sight.

01:26:55.966 --> 01:26:56.666
At first glance.

